title: peanut butter cookies(serves 6 dozen)
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth. Beat in sugar until blended, then eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat until well blended.
Chill dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk and butter.
Pour over all other ingredients except eggs.
Add eggs to pan with dry and liquid ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until a knife comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: chicken poppies
directions: Cook peas and carrots; drain. In large saucepan, cook onions and mushrooms in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, sage or thyme. Add chicken broth and milk all at once. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in drained peas and carrots and chicken. Pour chicken mixture into a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Top mixture with biscuits. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: quicky jambalaya
directions: Put rice, sausage and soups in 1 1/2 or 2-quart microwave dish. Cover; cook on High for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Pork, chicken or shrimp can be added.)

title: italian ham primavera
directions: Cook Rotini pasta in boiling water.
Mix contents of the broccoli pouch, ham, and vegetable blend into the pasta.
Continue cooking 5 minutes.
Drain, DO NOT RINSE.
Add cheese sauce and italian seasoning.
Cook until heated through, stirring occasionally.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk at rolling boil for 3 minutes, then add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix quickly and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: dill pickles(regular or kosher)
directions: Mix water, vinegar and salt well.
Put in quart jars dill, cloves, mustard seed and cloves of garlic.
Pack pickles loose in jars.
Pour cold brine over pickles (lided) and put into boiling water for 3 minutes.
Take out and tighten lids down.

title: country fried chicken (by dunkie)
directions: Mix flour, garlic salt, paprika, oregano, black pepper and salt.
Heat oil in skillet to 365°.
Beat egg and milk.
Mix flour and seasoning.
Dip chicken in milk and egg mixture, then dip into flour mixture.
Put into hot skillet and brown on both sides. Cover and simmer for tender chicken.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and milk together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Lay chicken on top.
Chop onion and sprinkle over top.
Cover with foil and bake for 2 or 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: baby food christmas cake
directions: Mix well; grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: pineapple do-nothing cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients, stirring to blend well.
No need to use mixer.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and buttermilk with soda and flour.
Roll out on floured board 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out and put on cookie sheet.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil
potatoes
in jackets, peel and grate.
Mix margarine, soup, onion, garlic, sour cream, salt, pepper and cheese with potatoes.
Top with cornflakes in melted butter.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: betty's chili
directions: Wash beans and place in large bowl covered by 2-inches of water. Soak overnight. Simmer in the same water until beans are tender. Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes more. Saute green peppers 5 minutes in oil. Add onions and cook until tender. In a large skillet, melt butter and saut beef 15 minutes (until done). Add meat to peppers and onions. Stir in chili powder and cook 10 minutes. Add this mixture to the beans. Season with salt, pepper and cumin seed. Simmer 1 hour. Remove cover and cook 30 more minutes.

title: spinach pom-poms
directions: Thaw spinach; drain.
Squeeze out all excess moisture.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts. Lightly grease baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 65.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and spices in mixing bowl. Drop in shortening and eggs.
Add applesauce and beat.
Add dates, raisins and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast raisin muffins
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add raisins and return to boil.
Cover, reduce heat, simmer 20 minutes and strain.
Drain; reserve liquid. Add water to measure 1/2 cup, if necessary.
Dissolve soda in liquid.
Combine flour, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Stir in raisins.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate-filled bonbons
directions: *For softer cookies, substitute 1/2 of the Crisco with margarine.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in mincemeat or other cooked fruit of your choice.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Cream mayonnaise and sugar.
Add sifted flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Stir in vanilla and hot water.
Bake for 30 minutes in hot oven (350°).

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add soups and milk.
Heat.
Place potatoes in a 3 quart pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with salt, black pepper, onion, bell pepper, and ham.
Pour heated soup mixture over potatoes and bake covered for 45 minutes at 325 degrees or until fork tender.
Uncover, top with cheese and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until melted but not brown.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Mix in blender until smooth and creamy.
Serve over your favorite salad.

title: black-eyed pea and sausage salad
directions: Thaw green peas.
Slice and quarter kielbasa.
Cover sausage with water in a saucepan and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool slightly.
Combine veggies and toss.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, let stand 3 hours.
Add the next 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Seal hot.

title: oil dressing
directions: Put in jar.
Shake before using.
Must be room temperature to use (refrigerate).
Best after few days old.

title: apple crunch
directions: Grease bottom of cake pan.
Fill 3/4 of pan with sliced apples.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Combine melted margarine or butter, brown sugar, oatmeal and flour.
Press mixture down over apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise, curry, nutmeg and Worcestershire sauce together; add chicken. Cook broccoli and drain.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Place broccoli in bottom, the rest of ingredients on top.
Serves 12.

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs and add corn syrup, salt, vanilla, brown sugar and butter; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake for an additional 30 to 35 minutes or until outer edge of filling seems set.
Let cool completely.
Before serving, put ring of whipped cream around edge of crust.

title: skillet lasagne
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Sprinkle half of sauce mix on beef. Spoon on cottage cheese.
Cover with uncooked noodles. Sprinkle on last half of sauce mix, basil, parsley and salt.
Break up tomatoes and pour over top.
Add the water.*

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: On waxed paper, mix flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken with mixture.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add pieces of chicken and cook slowly until browned on both sides.
Add soup and 1/2 cup water, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a bundt pan at 350° until done, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in bacon fat.
Remove pork chops to baking dish, pour can of condensed mushroom soup over them and onion. Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cottage pineapple pie(diet)
directions: Blend cottage cheese and pineapple juice to soften.
Add Knox unflavored gelatine until smooth.
Fold in pineapple, cottage cheese and vanilla.
Bake in graham cracker crust at 350° for 3 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: cool carrots
directions: Pour sauce over layered vegetables in 2-quart glass dish. Cover and refrigerate for up to 2 weeks (overnight before serving).

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt margarine, pour into dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and stir well. Add pecans and chips; stir.
Pour into crust and bake in 325° oven 20 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm if desired with whipped cream.
Very rich.
(Serve in small pieces.)

title: fudge nut brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, combine mix, flour, water, oil and egg.
By hand, stir with spoon until dough is formed.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from sheets; cool completely.
Frost cookies with chocolate frosting. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Combine sugars, flour and oatmeal in bowl.
Cut in peanut butter.
Add egg, vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Press into a well-greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Top with your favorite chocolate icing.
Makes about 20.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Put in pie pan.
Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk; beat 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture over crackers.
Layer graham crackers. Spoon remaining mix over crackers.
Layer graham crackers again. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Beat chocolate with syrup, vanilla, margarine, 3 tablespoons milk and confectioners sugar.
When smooth, ice the graham crackers and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients well. Add liquids which have been stirred together and stir until dry ingredients are well coated. Bake in a 300° oven, turning over in pan every 15 minutes.
Granola will be a golden color when done.
Stir once in pan when cooling.
Store in tightly covered containers.

title: orange balls
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crushed vanilla wafers; add sugar (reserving 1/2 cup), then frozen orange juice. Mix until blended and add finely chopped nuts. Continue mixing until all ingredients are evenly distributed. Form into 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in remaining confectioners sugar. Store in cool place in airtight container.

title: bagel bites(kids love 'em.)
directions: Cut each bagel into 6 thin slices about 1/4-inch thick. Preheat oven to 225°.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Bake about 1 hour or until crisp. Cool and store in an airtight container. Serve with Chunky Cheese Dip.

title: pot cheese kugel(double for crowd)
directions: Cook noodles and mix all ingredients together.
Melt 1/4 pound margarine in pan.
Roll about 15 cinnamon graham crackers to crumbs and mix margarine into it.
Spread on top of noodles.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Rinse in cold water and drain. Combine carrots, relish, salt and pepper with mayonnaise.
Pour over cooked macaroni and toss until well blended.
Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat the above ingredients for 2 minutes.
Place in a 9 by 13-inch pan.
Bake 350 degrees until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about one half hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add strawberries, thawed and thoroughly mashed.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat two minutes with electric mixer.
Stiffly beat egg whites.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Add to strawberry mixture.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed. Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy step pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar slowly, beating constantly to cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well and constantly. Stir in almond extract.
Turn batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for an hour and a half, or until cake is done.
Cool and serve.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and pecans; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in medium saucepan.
Let come to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Pour over oatmeal mixture; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: red cabbage citrus salad
directions: Arrange cabbage evenly on individual salad plates; place orange sections in center.
Sprinkle with pecans and green onions. Serve with dressing.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas punch(makes 8 to 10 cups)
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: impossibly easy coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a deep pie dish.
Pour all ingredients into blender.
Blend until well mixed.
Pour into buttered pie dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve cold.

title: wine spritzer
directions: Combine wine and soda or carbonated beverage.
Serve over ice. Makes 1 (about 8 ounce) serving.

title: chicken joes
directions: Add chopped onion to ground chuck and brown in skillet. Drain off grease. Add cream of chicken soup and diced cheese. Simmer on low heat 10 to 15 minutes. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Can add chopped nuts. Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: old fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Cover soup bones with water; heat to boiling and then simmer 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 1 hour longer or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bones and cut any meat from them and add to soup.

title: pinwheels(a very sweet treat)
directions: Cut butter and cream cheese into confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Knead, adding milk a tablespoon at a time, until dough is smooth and of a consistency where it can be rolled. Roll dough out flat; spread on peanut butter.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Cut into slices.
Store on wax paper layers.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients and add to liquids; mix well.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: spicy spuds
directions: Boil potatoes in skins (must still be firm).
Cool and grate. Place 1/2 in greased 9 x 13-inch pan with salt, pepper, onion and green pepper.
Repeat.
Add margarine and top with cream and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: make your own flavored rice mix
directions: Mix together. Store in covered jar or plastic bag in dry place. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons to water when cooking 1 cup rice.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until browned.
Mix next three ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Mix next two ingredients together.
Do not follow directions on pudding box.
Spread on crust on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top chocolate mixture with Cool Whip.
Top with chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: caramel torte
directions: Whip yolks until thick, adding sugar and rusk.
Stir in fluffy beaten egg whites.
Grease pan, add mixture and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Melt the Milk Duds and 1/4 cup margarine until smooth. Add 1/2 cup powdered sugar and pour over baked cake.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Prepare the three flavors of gelatin separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Place each flavor in 8-inch square pan and chill until firm.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until tender with a little bit of water; don't brown.
Set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add celery, onion and butter mixture.
Stir well. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Empty 1 can pork and beans into bottom of greased casserole. Combine sugar and mustard; sprinkle half of mixture over beans. Sprinkle rest of sugar/mustard mixture, chopped bacon and catsup over beans.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix butter and crumbs; press into large cake pan.
Cream sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Spread over crumb crust.
Layer in order:
bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip, pecans and cherries. Drizzle syrup over the top.
Freeze 2 hours.
Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil in a bowl; mix well.
Stir in zucchini, cinnamon, baking powder, flour, salt, baking soda, vanilla and nuts.
Spoon batter into 2 greased loaf pans (5 x 9-inch) or 1 (5 x 9-inch) and 3 mini loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date cake
directions: Mix flour with dates and nuts; add sugar.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Add well beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake slowly in tube pan at 300° to 320° for 1 hour.

title: spam and cheese sandwiches
directions: Shred cheese and Spam in bowl.
Add onion to taste.
Mix in enough Miracle Whip to form a thick but spreadable consistency spread.
Spread on bun halves and broil until edges just begin to burn and top is bubbly.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Set one
cup
of
cake mix aside and put remainder into large mixing
bowl
with	melted margarine and one beaten egg. Stir until consistency of cookie dough.	Spread into bottom of 11 x 13-inch cake pan and bake in 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes.
Take
the one cup of remaining cake mix and add 3 beaten eggs
and remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust like cake and bake for about 25 minutes.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into tube pan or bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Glaze with 1 cup confectioners sugar with either 2 tbsp milk or 2 tbsp lemon juice.

title: collards
directions: Remove leaves and roots.
Wash well and cook in boiling water seasoned with bacon fat, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook until tender.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Make into balls.
Cover with tomato soup mixed with water.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, breadcrumbs, egg, onion, salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1/8 teaspoon thyme.
Shape firmly into mini meat loaves.
Brown in skillet; pour off fat.
Stir in remaining soup, pepper, thyme and water.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir and baste occasionally.
I serve this with mashed potatoes, steamed broccoli and either canned peaches or pears for dessert.
Serves 4 to 6, depending on size of meat loaves.

title: no-fry eggplant parmesan
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Peel eggplants and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip in egg and dredge in meal.
Place in a single layer on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Turn eggplant slices and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: artichoke chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika; brown in butter.
Put chicken in casserole dish.
Add 1 teaspoon butter to drippings in pan and saute mushrooms.
Sprinkle flour on mushrooms.
Stir in broth, rosemary and sherry.
Cook for a few minutes.
Arrange drained artichokes between chicken.
Pour mushroom mixture over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 with rice.

title: stewed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into 2 to 3-inch lengths.
Put in covered saucepan.
Add water to cover carrots.
Add sugar and margarine. Cook on medium heat until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Combine sugar and oil; beat in egg and molasses.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons into shallow dish of sugar.
Place on baking sheet about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yellows; add lemon juice and beat well.
Add sweetened condensed milk and beat.
Let mixture sit while you beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually add the sugar and beat.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust and top with egg whites.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Let sit out for 10 minutes and then refrigerate.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into buttered glass baking dish. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: stuffing for slow cooker
directions: Cook on high for 1 hour, then on low.
The longer the better.

title: peanutty choco surprises
directions: Cream peanut butter, margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add gradually until well blended.
Chill dough at least 30 minutes for easier handling.
Wrap about 1 level teaspoonful of dough around each chocolate piece.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove and cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar and let cool.
Makes about 5 to 6 dozen.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute meat and vegetables until browned and tender.
Add cumin, chili powder and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Stir in rice.
Add enough water to the reserved tomato water to equal a total of 2 cups water.
Add to meat and rice mixture and heat until bubbling. Stir once more.
Lower heat to a simmer.
Cover and let cook 20 minutes until all moisture absorbed by rice.
Depending upon the consistency of rice desired, more or less water may be added.

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain thoroughly.
Blend with remaining ingredients and turn into a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients and lightly toss.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Sprinkle paprika for color.

title: mexican party dip
directions: On a round pizza pan, spread in order given.
Mix sour cream, taco seasoning and picante sauce.
Spread over the avocados.
Chop green onions and tomatoes for the fourth layer.
Spread sliced olives on top and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Use any chips. Serves about 20.

title: pizza pie
directions: To prepare dough, mix together the flour, salt and sugar. Place on a flat surface and form a hole in the center.
Mix the yeast and warm water and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add to the flour mixture and mix until you have a mound.
Make a depression in the mound and add 3/4 c. cool water and the olive oil.
Mix and knead to form a dough that is elastic and smooth.
If you don't achieve "elastic and smooth," use the dough anyway!
Put the dough into a greased, floured bowl and let it rest and raise for 30 minutes to an hour. Whether it raised or not, proceed as follows: Cut the dough into 4 pieces and flatten into a circle.
Put the pieces into pizza pie tins or separately on a large pizza pan.
If using tins, stretch the dough to the edge.
If using a large pizza pan, stretch the dough to individual serving size.
Spread each circle with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle liberally with cheese of your choice. Doctor up your little pizza with whatever you want, be creative!
Topping choices include pepperoni, salami, olives, cooked onions, cooked sausage, cooked ham strips, mushrooms, or arugula, the choices are endless.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12-15 minutes, until cheese is melted and your toppings are hot; start checking at 10 minutes.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Layer in order.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: sunday-dinner pot roast
directions: Place roast in deep roasting pan.
Cut up onions, potatoes and carrots.
Place around roast.
Pour soup and water over roast. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 hours or until tender.
Soup makes a great gravy.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, pineapple (including juice), sugar and Miracle Whip together with mixer until desired consistency is reached.

title: orange braised pork chops
directions: Coat chops with flour and salt and brown in oil, about 5 minutes on each side.
Combine brown sugar, ginger, orange peel and juice and pour over chops.
Simmer 45 to 50 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add orange slices and heat until orange sections are just warm.
Serve with Orange Rice.

title: sticky buns
directions: Defrost 2 loaves of bread dough.
Grease pan.
Pinch dough into small pieces.
Put in bottom of pan 1 loaf.
Mix milk, oleo, sugar, pudding and cinnamon over low heat until dissolved.
Pour over dough (first layer).
Save some mixture.
Pinch second loaf and place on top of first loaf.
Pour rest of mixture over second layer of dough.
Let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (on lower shelf).

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: vestal pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
This recipe makes 2 (9-inch) deep dish pies.
Mix all ingredients except pecans well.
Fold in pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake until set, approximately 45 minutes to an hour.
Center of pie will be slightly runny, but done when knife inserted comes out with grainy consistency.

title: donnie duke clark's corn bread dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add buttermilk until you have the consistency of pancake batter.
Add bacon drippings and 1 egg. Mix together and pour into a hot skillet with enough oil to barely cover bottom of skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, until cornbread is lightly browned and firm.
Makes enough dressing for 4 people.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour; boil and stir 1 minute.
Add all other ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp cocktail salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water; add V-8 juice.
Refrigerate until this stars to set.
Add all ingredients and pour into mold. Refrigerate.
Unmold and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients.
Do not use blender.

title: bean dish
directions: Place beans in baking dish.
Mix together sauce for beans in skillet and heat well, then pour over beans and mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef until done.
Drain.
Then add all ingredients together and cook until done.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cook and cube boneless chicken into small 1/2 to 1/4-inch cubes.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, melt butter; add onions and saute until tender.
Add flour and curry powder, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Stir in rest of ingredients; cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on tortilla shells. Roll up and place on a plate.
After all are done, refrigerate for a couple of hours.
Then just slice each one and serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil slowly a little over 1 hour.
When still juicy, but will sit up, quit cooking.
Pour into individual dishes or large bowl. Sprinkle with cinnamon and serve when cold.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Barely cook potatoes with skin on.
Cook onions and celery with butter and a little oil under tender.
Remove tough clams from minced mixture.
Combine in large pan:
clam chowder; pour light cream into empty can and fill to top with milk.
Fill second can to top with milk as well.
Combine milk, cream, Snow's, celery, dill and potatoes.
Cook for 30 plus minutes on low.
Do not boil.
When heated thoroughly add clams (washed and drained) and cook for 5 minutes.

title: peanut-sesame noodles
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions until al dente; rinse in cold water and drain well.
In food processor or blender, combine garlic, ginger, soy sauce, peanut butter, vinegar, honey, sesame oil and hot pepper sauce; process until blended.
Add water to reach desired consistency (1/2 to 3/4 cup), processing until smooth.
To serve, toss cooked linguine with vegetables and sauce. Yield:
6 servings.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and parsley.
Stir in potatoes.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mix salt, basil, pepper, orange juice, marjoram and garlic salt.
Pour over chicken breasts and marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Baste occasionally.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix Parmesan, flour, salt and pepper and shake in a bag.
Melt stick of butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shake potatoes in mixture, then place in dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops, in oil, in a large skillet that has a lid. Remove from oil and add rice.
Cook rice until brown.
Add onion and celery.
Continue to cook until vegetables are clear.
Add bouillon and salt; stir.
Lower heat to simmer.
Arrange pork chops in skillet over the rice.
Cover and cook for about 35 minutes, or until the rice is done.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well until well blended.
Form in balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about two inches apart.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields 90 servings.

title: never fail pie crust(houston junior league p 344)
directions: Sift flour with salt. Slowly dribble oil into flour, mixing with fork. Sprinkle water over dough and mix. Form into a ball and roll out between wax paper. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add orange peel, shortening, egg and orange juice.
Mix quickly, but well.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Blend.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: strawberry "de-lite" pie
directions: Slice strawberries; place in bottom of pie shell.
Mix well all dry ingredients in pan.
Add 1/2 cup hot water; bring to boil. Let cool, then pour over strawberries.
Top pie with Cool Whip. Refrigerate for at least 1/2 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour mixture into buttered individual size tin-foil loaf pans.
Bake at 350° oven for approximately 25-30 minutes.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.

title: finnish sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until real stiff.
Add Ghirardelli chocolate chips or mint chocolate chips.
Stir and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.

title: twelve day pickles
directions: First Day:
Pour 1 cup salt and boiling water to cover over cucumbers.

title: dream bars
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup flour.
Pat into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package.
Drain (approximately 3 1/2 cups).
Stir in margarine.
Add eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press spaghetti mixture in buttered 10-inch pie plate, forming crust.

title: tosca torte(finland-sweden)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs and sugar until the mixture is light and foamy.
Sift flour with baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Melt butter over low heat and let cool.
Add cream and melted butter to batter.
Butter and flour a round cake form or frying pan with high boards.
Pour butter into pan and cook until it is half done, about 20 minutes.

title: frozen pudding snacks
directions: Combine pudding mix, milk and peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Spread 1 tablespoon of pudding mixture on one half of a graham cracker.
Spread 1/2 tablespoon of Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture and top with other half of graham cracker.
Wrap individually in foil and freeze.
One sandwich contains 30 calories.

title: fried rice
directions: Add sesame oil to frying pan or wok.
Add vegetables and cook. Add soy sauce (several tablespoons).
Cook rice as directed on box, then add 2 tablespoons sesame oil to pan and brown rice, then add rice to cooked vegetables.
Add as much soy sauce as you like.

title: chocolate chip cookies(from country magazine)
directions: Beat oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and pudding mix.
Continue beating and add eggs and dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.

title: chocolate butterfinger cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in a rectangular pan.
While hot, poke holes in cake.
Pour condensed milk and caramel topping on cake.
When cool, top with Cool Whip and crushed Butterfinger.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add an ice ring if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peachy cinnamon coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease 8 inch square of 9 inch round baking pan. Drain peaches, reserving juice. Add water to reserved juice to equal 3/4 c. liquid. Chop peaches. Combine muffin mix, egg and 3/4 c. peach liquid in medium bowl; fold in peaches. Pour batter into pan. Knead

swirl packet 10 seconds before opening. Squeeze contents on top of batter and swirl with knife. Sprinkle topping over batter. Bake at 400° for 28 to 33 minutes for 8 inch pan or 20 to 25 minutes for 9 inch pan or until golden. Serve warm.

title: jello
directions: Put the jello stuff and water in a pan and stir.
Put it in the oven for 1 minute on high.
Take out of oven, put in freezer for 99 minutes.
Then eat it.

title: chocolate-peanut butter pile-ups
directions: For a sweeter bar, use 1 cup sugar.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda together.
Cut in shortening. Soften yeast in water.
Mix yeast and buttermilk with dry ingredients.
Roll out to 1/4-inch and cut.
Place in 400° oven (cold).
Dip in melted butter and fold for butterfly rolls.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Bring 2 1/2 cups of water to boiling.
Add rice pilaf and seasoning from package.
Add hamburg and 1 can of mushroom soup. Place in buttered casserole dish or spray with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Press down with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beet relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan; bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes.
Can in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: fat-free stuffed pasta shells
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms, garlic and oregano.
Add turkey and sausage.
Cook on medium heat.
Add Prego sauce.
Pour mixture into a bowl.
Add Romano cheese.
Boil jumbo pasta shells until firm.
Stuff mixture into shells, then cover heavily with Mozzarella cheese.
Heat in oven for 10 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix strawberry-banana jello like regular only use juice of little can of drained crushed pineapple and juice from small carton of strawberries, that is packed with juice, for cold water part of jello directions.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Beat the butter, Crisco, white chocolate, almond flavoring, white vanilla and salt together.
Then add confectioners sugar (beat into the mixture a little at a time) and cream or evaporated milk (add as needed to mix).
This recipe can be used to decorate as well as ice cakes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring once after the corn pudding begins to cook.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Shred zucchini to measure 2 cups; set aside.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder; mix well.
Add raisins and nuts to dry ingredients.
Combine with zucchini mixture; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack to cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fudge
directions: Boil the sugar, cocoa, milk and corn syrup over medium-high heat.
When a drop of this mixture in a glass of cold water forms a firm ball, it is cooked.
Add the butter, vanilla and Marshmallow Fluff (heaping).
Stir this over heat until melted. Immerse pan in cold water until it begins to thicken.
Pour quickly into greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: tea house pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and milk alternately, beating well. Add flavorings. Pour batter into a greased and floured large tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: potato soup(6 to 10 servings)
directions: Fry bacon in a 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat.
Remove bacon from pot when crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Strain out all but 1 tablespoon of bacon fat and discard.
Saute onion in remaining bacon fat until tender and golden, about 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, celery, carrots, 3 cups water and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt to pot.
Cover; cook over high heat until mixture comes to a boil, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; simmer for 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Drain in colander.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Pour warm water in large bowl. Sprinkle yeast then add sugar and salt. Stir. Add 2 c. flour and mix thoroughly. Add 1 egg and stir, followed by 1 c. flour. Mix thoroughly. Add melted oleo and stir. Add 1 1/4 c. flour and mix thoroughly. Let
rise until double in size. Make out rolls using remaining 3/4 c. flour. Put in buttered pan (13 X 9). Let rise again until double in size and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate until well chilled.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dot with butter and crushed crackers.
I use bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° in casserole dish until top is golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine ketchup, vinegar, horseradish, brown sugar, garlic and thyme.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium-low heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until thickened, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in pepper.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Fill Dutch oven 2/3 full of water.
Add chicken, celery, onion and carrots.
Cook until done.
Remove chicken and cut up. Add noodles and bouillon cubes.
Add chicken.
May need to add more water.
Cook until noodles are tender.

title: pear pecan salad
directions: Drain juice from pears and reserve 1 cup of liquid.
Bring the juice to a boil, remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Chill until partially set.
Place cheese and pears in blender and blend until creamy.
Stir in Jell-O mixture.
Add pecans and whipping cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into mold.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt oleo and add brown sugar.
Cool.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel and slice apples; put into cold, salty water.
Rinse and cook apples until soft and mushy.
Add one cup sugar to a cup of cooked apples; add cinnamon to taste.
Cook until thick and dark. Put into jars and cool.

title: lemonade syrup
directions: Juice lemons and cut rind of 2 of them into slices.
Combine in a pan the water, sugar and salt.
Add 2 lemons; sliced.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes and cool.
Add juice.
Strain and store in covered jar in the refrigerator.

title: hot portuguese rice
directions: Place all ingredients, except meat, in pan and cook over a low fire.
Add meat, stir and cook until meat is browned.
Fill pan to 2/3 full of water.
Bring to a boil and put in as much rice as you prefer.
Add paprika to color.
Cook slowly for one hour.

title: potatoes and cheese
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese and margarine.
Fold in potatoes and place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles and cheese is melted.

title: delicious coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs singly, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with sour cream, blending after each addition.
Spread 1/2 of batter in a 10-inch tube pan that has been lined with waxed paper.
Cream margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Add nuts and mix well.
Dot batter in pan evenly with 1/2 of nut mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Dot with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: inside out ravioli(your kids will eat spinach!)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Meanwhile, brown and drain ground beef.
Add tomato paste, spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Defrost and squeeze spinach.
Crumble on top of noodles. Spoon cheese spread into small clumps on top of spinach.
Cover with sauce/meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Combine dry ingredients. Add shortening, yeast mixture and milk.
Mix well.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Cut out biscuits with biscuit cutter or floured rim of a glass.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 10.

title: fruit salad & dressing
directions: Toss salad ingredients together in bowl.

title: caribbean chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Brown chicken. Reduce heat to low.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour, stirring and adding water as necessary. Serve over rice.

title: mama's eggless fruit cake
directions: Mix butter
and sugar.	Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add
vanilla,	nuts
and raisins.
Bake in 4 layer pans that
have
been
greased
and floured and line the bottom with wax
paper.
Bake
for 30 to 40 minutes. (Watch it.) Turn out of pan to cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: *Try substituting fresh strawberries.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs then other ingredients. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lush dessert
directions: Mix together the butter, flour and chopped nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; let cool before next layer.

title: orange-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole combine brown sugar, orange drink powder, cornstarch and water.
Cook at High for 2 minutes, until mixture is thickened and bubbly, stirring after one minute.
Stir in butter.
Add potatoes, stirring to coat.
Cook at High for 4 minutes, until heated through, turning each potato over once. Makes 4 servings.

title: spiced shrimp
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp. Stir gently.
Cover and steam until tender, approximately 10 minutes for small and 20 minutes for large shrimp.
Drain.
If not shelled, remove shells and vein in back.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Roll out on a floured surface. Cover and let dry 3 to 4 hours.
Roll out to approximately 1/8-inch thick.
After dough is dry, roll up and cut into thin noodles. Unroll and mix slowly in boiling broth.
Cook approximately 20 to 25 minutes until tender.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Slice onion in sauce. Add sliced cucumber and chill.

title: sauerkraut und speck(sauerkraut with pork; old dutch recipe)
directions: Wipe pork with damp cloth; place in large stewing pan and cover with cold water.
Set over flame to cook slowly for 1 hour. Add sauerkraut and more water, if necessary, and continue cooking for another hour or until meat has become thoroughly tender. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: rice pudding jerry
directions: Cook rice until tender, adding water as necessary.
Cook for 1 to 2 hours.

title: basic barbecued spareribs
directions: To prepare ribs: Simmer in a large pot with salted water to cover for 45 to 60 minutes, until meat begins to pull away from bones.
In a bowl, combine sauce.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Place ribs on deep platter; brush sauce on both sides.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Remove ribs.
Pour sauce in a cup.
Cook by barbecuing time table to desired doneness, brushing frequently with sauce.
Serves 6.

title: mom's coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt. Slowly add milk. Stir together well. Cook in heavy saucepan over medium heat until mixture thickens and coats the back of a wooden spoon. (Stir constantly while cooking this mixture.) Remove from heat. Beat egg yolks. Slowly add 1 cup of filling to egg yolks while stirring. Add egg yolk mixture to the remaining filling in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring well, until filling thickens and a spoon leaves a trail in the filling when stirred. Add vanilla, margarine and coconut. Pour into baked shell. Use egg whites to make your favorite meringue. Top filling with meringue and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until meringue is browned.

title: quick mexican microwave snack
directions: Take 1 tortilla shell; spread with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar (as much as you like).
Form shell into a roll. Heat in microwave for 30 seconds.
Enjoy!

title: cheesy au gratin potatoes
directions: Saute onion, water in skillet. Add frozen hash browns; cook until no longer frozen. Mix cream cheese, soup and milk; mix with the hash browns. Place in greased 9 x 13 inch pan and sprinkle with cheddar cheese. Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: aunt sue's overnight lettuce salad
directions: Layer first six ingredients.
Spread mayonnaise on top. Sprinkle with sugar, cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, nuts and mayonnaise; toss.
If desired, mound salad in lettuce cups and garnish with maraschino cherry halves.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apricot ice
directions: Blend in blender (it will be full to the top but doesn't go over).
Pour into a glass (not plastic or aluminum) dish and freeze.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Set out about half hour before serving.

title: easy party rolls
directions: Place rolls in freezer for a little while.
Slice entire package of rolls in half horizontally.
Place ham and cheese on bottom half.
Replace top half.
Melt butter.
Add other ingredients to melted butter and stir.
Pour over rolls. Refrigerate overnight.
May be frozen then thawed in refrigerator. Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.
Slice.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cinnamon crumbs and butter together.
Press into bottom of spring-form pan with fingers and slightly up sides.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If you need the sauce immediately, it may be cooked in the microwave.
Otherwise, just put it in the refrigerator for several days.

title: cinnamon snack
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
In a 9 x 9-inch pan, tear biscuits apart into pieces.
Add syrup and butter.
Mix up. Sprinkle with the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes and eat hot.

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: Drain and flake the tuna.
Set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Combine noodles with tuna, celery and green onions.
Blend in the sour cream, mustard, mayonnaise, thyme and salt.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until onions start to brown. Add beef.
Let brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil. Simmer 3 hours with cover on.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Peel and grate zucchini.
Boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add sugar, pineapple and lemon juice; boil 6 minutes. Remove from heat, add jello.
Put in jars or put in refrigerator.

title: rice goulash
directions: Brown beef with onion in 10-inch skillet; drain off fat.
Stir in water, rice, crushed bouillon cubes and dry mustard.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Stir in green pepper and tomato.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: low country boil
directions: Cut sausage 3-inches long.
Cook in skillet.
Prepare potatoes; wash, remove spots, but don't peel; cut lengthwise. Prepare corn, cut in half.
Cook potatoes.
Add corn and sausage. Add seasoning.
Rinse shrimp well.
Add to boil.
Cook 10 minutes. Boil; serves 6 to 8 people.
(Serve with green salad, French or garlic bread.)

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Set chocolate chips aside.
Cream margarine, oil and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Spread in greased rectangular cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna-cheese-vegetable bake
directions: Spread tuna in ungreased 9-inch square pan or 1 1/2 to 2-quart shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.

In medium saucepan, combine soup, peas, celery, milk and onion; heat to simmering. Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits; cut each into fourths. Pour hot soup over tuna and cheese; arrange biscuits over soup. Drizzle with butter (I usually use squeeze margarine); top with potato chips (I usually just take a few handfuls and crush then to cover).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except crust.
Pour into crust; refrigerate.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with shredded Velveeta cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients, stirring frequently, until margarine is melted.
Makes about 3/4 cup sauce; 50 calories per tablespoon.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Put half in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Pour one jar Pizza Sauce over meat.
Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Stir in egg and pour on top of meat.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Add rest of meat, jar of sauce and whatever other toppings you like.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: brownies #1
directions: In
a
large
mixing bowl, combine the flour and sugar. In
a heavy
saucepan,
combine butter, shortening, coffee or water
and cocoa.
Stir
and
heat
to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar in the bowl.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well, using a wooden spoon
or
high
speed on
electric
mixer.
Pour into a well buttered
pan.
Bake
at 400° for 20 minutes or until brownies test
done in the center. Frost while still warm with brownie frosting.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: lemon lush cake
directions: Mix nuts, flour and oleo together.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar. Add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix milk and pudding together until thick.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Sprinkle with some finely chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: chops for hungry chap
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Fry in a large skillet; add chops and brown very slowly on both sides.
Leave out.
Add water; sprinkle with salt and arrange chops over rice.
Sprinkle with remaining salt.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Spoon on corn; sprinkle with pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down to low and cover and simmer 25 to 35 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add small amount of water if mixture cooks dry.

title: best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixing bowl, beat butter, sugars and cocoa until well blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.

title: cocktail mix
directions: Mix all (except crackers) together (mix in a brown paper bag). Pour over crackers and store in tight container.

title: prune cake, prestige
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend together thoroughly sugar and vegetable oil. Add eggs, one at a time, to sugar mixture and blend after each addition. Sift together flour, soda, nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon and salt. Add dry ingredients to sugar-egg mixture alternately with mixture of buttermilk and vanilla extract. Fold in prune pulp and pecans. Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon carrot cake
directions: Peel and slice carrots. Cook abut 20 minutes until tender. Mash carrots with potato masher. Grease and flour three 9-inch pans. Set aside.

title: karen's mushroom log
directions: Mix cream cheese, mushroom pieces and seasoning salt together. Set aside.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes without salt.
Mash with a little milk and butter. Mix all other ingredients (except Velveeta cheese) with the mashed potatoes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread half of the potato mixture.
Layer Velveeta cheese slices.
Top with remaining potato mixture. Dot with butter and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, flour, liquid and vinegar.
Cook, stirring, on medium heat until thick, about 10 minutes.
Add salt, butter or margarine and then beets.
Cover and heat.
Serve.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Combine macaroni and next 5 ingredients; pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle evenly over macaroni mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add finely chopped green onions, pecans and dried beef.
Knead until well mixed.
Shape in ball and chill overnight.

title: finger salad
directions: Spread crescent rolls in a 13 x 9-inch pan, press and bake according to directions.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix and spread over pressed rolls.
Toss raw vegetables, then spread over creamy mixture.
Place broccoli and cauliflower last.
Let set in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: smothered frog legs
directions: Slowly brown frog legs in butter.
Add salt, pepper and onions and cook until brown.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf, thyme, parsley and garlic.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Add bell peppers and water.
Continue to smother until frog legs are tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Prepare hot roll mix according to package directions, adding butter, raisins, fruit and peels, sugar and spices to flour mixture; mix well.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise in warm place until double (about 1 hour).
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth.
Shape in 12 buns.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until almost double, about 45 minutes.
Using sharp scissors (or knife), snip top of buns to form shallow cross.
If a glaze is desired, brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° about 15 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly; form crosses with Confectioners Sugar Icing.
Makes 12 buns.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar gradually. Cream well. Add egg, almond and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add to first mixture. Blend. Roll gently 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out.
Bake on oiled sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, shortening and salt until it forms crumbs and set it aside.
Save 1 cup of crumbs for topping.
Mix hot water, baking soda and molasses in a large bowl.
Blend in the remaining crumbs with the liquid.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of crumbs on top before baking.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let it cool to cut.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine dressing mix, dill weed, oil and oyster crackers. Stir to coat. Place on cookie sheet.
Place in a 250° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir gently halfway through baking.
Cool and store in covered tin or large Ziploc bag.

title: beef hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly mix all ingredients, except cheese, in large frying pan.
Cook on low heat until underside is lightly browned.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole, which has been sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Top with cheese.
Heat in oven for 10 minutes to melt cheese.

title: banana nut cookies(yield:  4 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well with a wire whisk.
Set aside.
In large bowl with an electric mixer, blend sugars at medium speed.

Add butter and mix to form a grainy paste, scraping down the sides of the bowl. Add egg, liqueur and banana and beat at medium speed until smooth. Add the flour mixture, 1 cup of the chocolate chips and the walnuts and blend at low speed until just combined.
Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Sprinkle cookies with chocolate chips, 6 to 8 per cookie.
Bake 25 to 27 minutes or until cookie edges begin to brown.
Transfer immediately to a cool surface with a spatula.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind together and let stand for several days in refrigerator.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles for 8 minutes.
Cool with water.
Cook meat and drain.
Stir in sauce and water.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine in small bowl the cottage cheese, Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper.

title: frank perdue's favorite sweet 'n smoky chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place onion slices in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken in a single layer, skin side up, on top of onion.
Sprinkle with hickory salt and pepper.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let set 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix together with rest of ingredients and cook until tender.
Drain off excess juice.
Pack in jars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in greased casserole, top with pats of butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When it's cooled, corn will rise and look fluffy.

title: herb tea brew
directions: Pour boiling water over the tea bags and steep for 5 minutes. Place brewed tea in a large pitcher or other container. Add enough water to equal one gallon. Serve over ice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Add bananas and beat.
Add flour and soda; mix together and add nuts.
Makes two (2) bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: custard sauce
directions: Heat milk, sugar and a few grains salt in top of double broiler.
Beat egg yolks slightly; add some of the heated milk. Mix and pour back into remaining milk.
Place over hot, not boiling water.
Cook, stirring constantly until custard coats metal spoon. Remove at once; add vanilla and place pan in bowl of cold water. Stir occasionally until cool.
Makes about 2 cups.
Great over jello, pound cake, etc., for easy dessert.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Cook hamburger meat and sausage in separate pans until done. Drain off excess fat.
Spread a layer of hamburger meat in bottom of pie pastry, then one-half chopped onion, Cheddar cheese, sausage, rest of onion and then Mozzarella cheese.
In a small bowl, mix half and half, whipping cream, egg, salt and pepper. Pour over filled pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° or until crust is golden brown.

title: saucy steak skillet
directions: Coat beef steak pieces with flour; pound into beef.
Brown beef in oil in 10-inch skillet.
Push beef to side.
Cook and stir onion in oil until tender; drain.
Add enough water to reserved potato liquid to measure 1 cup.
Mix potato liquid, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, pepper flakes, instant bouillon, salt, marjoram and pepper. Pour on beef and onion.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crisco white icing *
directions: Beat egg white until stiff, then add 10x sugar, Crisco and vanilla.
Beat all together.
Add 10x sugar until stiff enough to spread.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: In mixer bowl, beat butter for 30 seconds to soften. Add the brown sugar and beat until fluffy. Beat in flour and nuts. Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.

title: easy onion soup
directions: Cut each onion in half from stem to root, then slice thinly crosswise.
Cook onion and butter covered on high 15 minutes, stirring twice.
Add undiluted beef broth and 1 cup water.
Cook covered on high 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix cheese and parsley. Arrange toast on baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese mixture.
Bake just until cheese melts.
Ladle soup into 4 soup bowls.
Top each with toast slice.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and eggs.
Add onion and one half of tomato sauce.
Form into a loaf in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
In saucepan combine topping ingredients; bring to boil.
Pour over meat loaf; bake 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, oats, soda, sour cream, baking powder, flour, cinnamon, pecans and raisins in bowl; mix well, adding more flour, if necessary.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Use bean dip for bottom layer.
Mash avocado with lemon juice and use for second layer.
Include sour cream in second layer. Combine taco seasoning, mayonnaise, onion and tomato for top layer.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: diabetic baked ginger pears
directions: Drain pears and reserve juice; set aside.
Combine brown sugar substitute, 1/2 teaspoon ginger, lemon juice and pecans.
Stuff pear halves with mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 teaspoon ginger.
Place pear halves close together in a nonstick baking dish.
Pour reserved pear juice to cover bottom of dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.
Yields 8 servings.
Each serving may be exchanged for 1 fruit and 1 fat.

title: presto party franks
directions: Slice franks into a mixture of currant jelly and mustard. Heat and serve.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Separate egg; beat the yolk and add to ingredients.
Add hot milk.
Beat egg white and fold into mixture.
Pour in 9-inch pie crust shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Bake another 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot relish *
directions: Boil carrots in salt water until fork-tender.
Cool.
Mix with pepper and onion.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Mix all together. Keeps a long time refrigerated.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil the tea, cinnamon and cloves in water for 2 minutes. Remove tea bags, cinnamon and cloves.
Add sugar and juices. Serve hot.
Makes 1 gallon. Can store or reheat.

title: cheese spread
directions: In medium bowl mix all ingredients until blended smooth. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chicken cranberry salad
directions: Grease 8 or 9-inch square pan with mayonnaise.
Combine chicken, celery, salt, pepper, cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice and almonds in large mixing bowl.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Combine gelatin with cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add hot water, stir to dissolve gelatin.
Add to chicken mixture.
Press into pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions. Stir in soup, tuna and peas. Mix well. Heat until bubbly.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In large bowl, combine vanilla frosting, peanut butter and margarine with fork until well blended.
Stir in crumbs until well mixed.
Form into 1-inch balls; chill 1 hour.

title: popovers
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Add eggs and milk. Beat for 2 minutes and pour into hot, greased muffin tins.
Bake about 25 minutes in hot oven.

title: french vanilla fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice. Drain oranges and chop bananas. Mix pudding and juice together. Pour this mixture over the fruit.

title: mini cherry cheesecake
directions: Place wafers in baking cups or containers for cupcakes.
Mix other ingredients (cream cheese, vanilla, sugar, then eggs).
Pour into baking cup 1/2 full.
Put in 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool and top it off with cherries.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in large saucepan until transparent and tender.
Add soup and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well.
Simmer on low heat, stirring occasionally so not to scorch, or low in crock-pot.

title: hot turkey or chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: glazed peach pie
directions: Mash peaches to make 1 cup.
Blend sugar and corn starch and cook with orange juice and lemon juice until thick.
Cool.
Put some glaze in shell.
Add peaches and pour rest of glaze over it. Refrigerate 3 hours. Serve with whip cream.
Can use blueberries, raspberries, or strawberries instead of peaches.

title: irish potato pie
directions: Mix and cook in unbaked pie shell until pie sets (as custard). The pie is done when a knife inserted will come out clean.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat shortening and peanut butter until creamy. Gradually add sugars, beating thoroughly after each addition. Beat in egg and vanilla. Mix remaining ingredients and blend into peanut butter mixture. Shape dough into balls about 1-inch in diameter. Place about 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet. Flatten each cookie. Crisscross top of each cookie with a fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from sheet while warm.

title: stir-fry shrimp with linguine
directions: Cover bottom of large skillet or wok with approximately 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Stir-fry the shrimp, mushrooms, bell pepper and garlic until shrimp are pink.
Add the cooked linguine, seasonings and capers.
Stir quickly together with Parmesan cheese just until the linguine is heated.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Stir in sugar, melted margarine and remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice in salad oil in a skillet until brown.
Add soy sauce, bouillon cubes, water and salt.
Cover; simmer 15 to 18 minutes.
Now add chicken, green pepper, celery and onion.
Cover; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve Jell-O; add tomatoes.
Chill slightly; add remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan and chill.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix 1 cup of the sugar, bourbon and corn syrup.
Add wafers and nuts.
Stir until evenly moistened.
Pinch walnut-sized pieces from the mix and roll firmly between palms to form a ball.
Sift remaining 1/2 cup sugar with cocoa onto wax paper.
Roll balls in mixture.
Store in airtight container with wax paper between layers.
Makes about 50 balls.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and chili.
Top with cheddar cheese, microwave for two minutes.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: In a large bowl, mix the cheese, beef, 4 onions plus the green tops, chopped up fine, then add the garlic salt, Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix all by hand.
Serve on Town House crackers.
Tastes better than it looks!

title: sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, melt 5 tablespoons margarine in oven. Stir in brown sugar and water. Separate each can of crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal. Spread with 3 tablespoons softened margarine. Combine cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle over dough. Starting at shorter side, roll up each rectangle. Cut each roll into 4 slices, forming 32 pieces.
Place, cut side down, in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Invert immediately. Serve warm.

title: creamed sauerkraut
directions: Drain and rinse sauerkraut.
Save about 1/4 cup of rinsed liquid for thickening.
Dice onion and simmer until golden brown. Stir in sauerkraut in same pan as onions (low heat).
Mix flour and liquid.
Pour into sauerkraut and onions.
Stir until liquid thickens.
Simmer a little longer.
Enjoy with pork or kielbasa.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Boil 4 cups water with the sugar until sugar is dissolved; cool.
Add remaining ingredients, except maraschino cherries and orange slices; pour into punch bowl over ice.
Decorate top of punch with cherries and orange slices.
Serves 30.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; blend with mixer.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: codfish balls
directions: Cut codfish into strips; place in medium saucepan with 1 1/2 to 2 cups water, bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 5 minutes; drain.
Separate fish strips into small flakes.
Place in medium saucepan with potatoes and 1 1/2 cups water; bring to boiling.
Boil gently, covered, for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Turn into strainer to drain very well. In medium bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat fish mixture until very smooth.
Add egg, butter and pepper; beat until well combined.

In electric skillet or heavy saucepan, slowly heat salad oil (from 1 1/2 to 2 inches deep) to 385° on deep frying thermometer; gently drop fish mixture, by heaping tablespoonfuls 5 or 6 at a time, into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, about 1 minute.
With slotted spoon, remover fish balls as they brown, drain on paper.
Makes about 2 dozen; 6 servings.

title: melon wedges
directions: Cut melon in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds and drain well. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in fruit.
Pour into melon halves. Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: inexpensive punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Enough for 35
servings.

title: upside-down apple pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In 9 inch pie pan, combine pecans, brown sugar and margarine; spread evenly over bottom of pan. Prepare pie crust according to package directions for two-crust pie, placing bottom crust over pecan mixture in pan.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, powdered sugar, egg and salt.
Mix well.
Add oil, oleo, vanilla and flour.
Drop by teaspoon; press down with bottom of small glass covered in sugar.
Bake at 350°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half; place ham and cheese on bottom layer of rolls.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over ham and cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute on high with hand mixer.
Pour over meat mixture in pie plate.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add a couple drops of Tabasco sauce to taste, plus salt and pepper as desired.
Shake to mix. Refrigerate after using.
Will keep well.

title: robert redford dessert
directions: For first layer, mix first 4 ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and spread on crust.
Mix pudding and milk together and pour onto second layer. Top with remainder of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: hershey's disappearing cake
directions: *May substitute self-rising flour and omit baking powder, baking soda and salt.

title: company strada
directions: Put scraps of bread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer cheese on top of that.
Next, put the broccoli and the ham. Arrange the donuts and holes on top.
Combine the eggs, salt, milk and dry mustard.
Pour over bread and cover with Saran Wrap. Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: company casserole
directions: Butter or spray a 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Wash rice and scatter over bottom of pan.
Cover rice with cut up pieces of chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over the chicken.
Dilute cream of mushroom soup with hot water, and pour over the chicken.
Cover pan lightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours, or 350° for 2 hours, or 400° for 1-1/4 to 1-1/2 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: salsa pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In very large bowl mix pasta, tomatoes, onion, peppers and undrained chili peppers, olives and mix well.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Melt the butter and combine with the corn muffin mix, the cream ed corn, whole kernel corn, the sour cream and the eggs (slightly beaten).
Pour it into 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
If it is a little soft in the center, bake 5 minutes longer.

title: bacon cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon in 1 1/2-quart casserole microwave dish.
Heat on full power 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir halfway through heating time.
Beat until smooth with wire whip if necessary.
Stir in bacon.
Pour in desired container and chill.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cut shrimp into bite size pieces.
Add celery and eggs. Combine the rest; spoon over shrimp.
Mix gently.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Drain pineapple, save juice; add enough water to make 3 1/2 cups.
Boil juice mixture and sugar; add cranberries and cool 7 to 10 minutes.
Stir in gelatin. Mix well.
Add grapes, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Combine and simmer 15 minutes until warm.
Add chipped ham.

title: peach cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in 2 layers.
Cool and split layers.
Mix dry frosting mix and whipping cream in cold mixing bowl until stiff.
Fold in peaches.
Frost between layers. Refrigerate.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Cook the lima beans, small green peas and French cut beans and drain.

title: easter braid
directions: Mix flour, salt, 5 Tbsp. sugar, & shortening together.
Add fruit, dates, nuts, and orange peel.
Divide the fruit ingredients into 3 equal portions in separate bowls.
Divide yeast equally into 3 cups.
Add 1 Tbsp. sugar into each yeast cup. Add 2 Tbsp. lukewarm water to each yeast cup to soften the yeast.
Add a few drops of 1 food coloring to each of the yeast cups.
In each yeast cup, add 1 Tbsp. flour to make a batter.
Divide lukewarm milk into 3 equal parts.
To each 1/3 fruit mixture, add 1 cup of yeast mixture and 1 portion of lukewarm milk.
Knead until well mixed and a soft dough is formed.
Grease bowls and dough.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Punch down & let rise again. divide each bowl of dough into 3 equal portions.
Roll each portion into ropes;
about 9 inches long.
Then braid (1 piece of each color) forming a loaf.
Place in greased loaf pans, allowing bread to double in size.
Bake in 350°F. oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix together fruit and pudding in a large bowl.
Add Cool Whip, as mush as desired.
Refrigerate until served.

title: window wash
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
In west Texas make sure distilled water is used.
Blue food coloring is an option.
Put the mixture in a spray bottle.

title: crab canapes
directions: Drain and press moisture from crab meat.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Spread mixture on muffin halves.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze 1 hour.
(Can freeze longer if making ahead.)
Remove from freezer and cut into quarters.
Broil 2 to 3-inches from broiler, until brown and bubbly.

title: holiday nuts
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and boil until soft ball forms when dropped in water. Then add vanilla and pecan halves; stir together. Pour and spread over wax paper to cool.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Bake chocolate cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into paper-lined cupcake tins 2/3 full.
In small bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and salt together.
Then add chocolate chips.
This makes the filling.
Drop 1 teaspoon of filling in each cupcake. Bake as regular cupcakes, then frost.
Makes 36 cupcakes.

title: a meal in one casserole
directions: In
a
casserole
dish,
flatten
uncooked ground meat. (Season meat
as
desired
with salt, pepper and onion).
Pour tomato sauce
on ground meat evenly.
Pour beans, then corn on top of	tomato	sauce.	Next,
mix your favorite cornbread mix and pour
on top of all ingredients.
Spread evenly.
Place in oven at 350°.
Bake 45 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: golfer's chicken
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and pour over chicken.
This can be cooked, covered, in a 325° oven for one hour.
Then uncover and cook until browned and tender.

title: oven baked beans
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large shallow baking pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs, vanilla and cooled raisins.
Combine the flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add the dry ingredients to raisin mixture and then add nuts, if desired. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Batter is best to work with if refrigerated for awhile before baking.

title: pate wellington
directions: Mash liver sausage and mix in Worcestershire sauce and green onion.
Carefully unwrap crescent rolls but do not divide into triangles.
Make 4 rectangles (2 triangles each).
Pinch perforations to seal.
Place a quarter of the liver sausage mixture into each rectangle.
Fold in ends to meet and pinch to seal.
Place loaves on ungreased baking sheet, seam side down. Brush tops with egg and prick to allow steam to escape.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve with a light side salad as an hors d'oeuvre or lunch.
