title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.	Bake in oven 1 hour or until done.

title: snow peas(edible pea pods)
directions: Stem and string fresh snow peas (leave them whole); or thaw frozen peas with hot water.
Simmer in 1/4 cup water about 3 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into peas.
Cover and cook 3 to 4 minutes longer, or until peas are tender-crisp.

title: salisbury steak bake
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 6 or 8 patties.
Place in a shallow baking pan, 12 x 9-inch. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Mix remaining soup with 1/3 cup water.
Pour over meat.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: chili con carne
directions: Turn heat on high and cook the water out of the meat.
Remove from heat and add spices and flour.
Blend all together, then add water slowly.
Turn on heat to medium-high until it begins to thicken, then turn down to low and cook slowly, but stirring occasionally.
The flavor is even better if made a day ahead. Cook 1 to 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Blend well. Add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Mix well; shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in salt, flour and baking powder. Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll around and shape into a ball.
Place about 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: tortillas for tacos
directions: Roll out like pie crust and cook in hot skillet like pancakes. (No oil in skillet.)

title: turkey enchiladas
directions: In a medium bowl, combine turkey, half the enchilada sauce, chilies, onion flakes, and cilantro.
Spoon two heaping tablespoons of the mixture down the center of each tortilla.
Roll tortillas jelly-roll style to seal.
Spray 9x13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Place tortillas seam-side down in dish.
Top tortillas with remaining enchilada sauce, onions, tomato, olives, and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Combine and blend cream cheese and milk.
Add crabmeat (I always pick over just in case some cartilage has been overlooked), onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Blend well by hand or by blender and spoon into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or party rye bread.
(May be made a day ahead and heated before serving.)

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and molasses.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add dry mixture alternately with milk.
When well mixed, roll and pat in greased pan 3/8-inch thick (should make 7 to 8 layers).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, egg and milk.
Blend in well drained cherries.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Use a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: sarah's hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped pecans and bananas.

title: steve's liver stuffing for squabs
directions: Cream the butter; add eggs.
Add the livers, finely chopped, and the hearts, if desired.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add enough bread crumbs to form a soft dressing that will drop from the spoon.
Makes enough dressing for 6 squabs.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix water and cornstarch, then set aside.
Grease baking dish.
Slice apples into dish.
Mix sugar and cinnamon, then sprinkle evenly over apples.
Pour water and cornstarch mixture on top.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken; remove from stock.
Add bouillon cubes, cilantro, taco seasoning, onions, salt, pepper, corn and tomatoes. Shred chicken and add to soup.
Put some Tostitos in a bowl. Sprinkle cheese on top; spoon soup over that.

title: chocolate cake(by cliffus ferguson)
directions: Mix cocoa and water; stir until smooth.
Set aside.
Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add soft butter and cream well.
Add cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Add flour and sour milk gradually. Beat well.
Bake in two layers, about 350°, until brown.

title: bread pudding(old fashion)
directions: Put crumbs in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Blend into warm milk, butter, sugar, eggs, salt, cinnamon and raisins. Place baking dish in oblong cake pan of warm water 1-inch deep. Bake at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean, 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with sauce.

title: dilly dip for raw vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Better if allowed to set overnight.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine ingredients, all but sour cream, after jello has dissolved in water.
Pour into bowl and let set. Top with sour cream or leave plain.
You can also pour a layer of jello and let set, pour sour cream on top and then pour rest of jello mixture on top and let set.
(This salad can be split in half.)
Easy and good.

title: apple butter sweet potatoes
directions: Prepare sweet potatoes; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cook in lightly salted boiling water to cover until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and let cool.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Brown
chicken pieces in oil.
Combine remaining ingredients and
pour over chicken in skillet.	Cover and simmer 30 to	40 minutes
or
until	tender.
Baste occasionally.
Skim excess fat from sauce before serving.

title: liquor-irish cream
directions: Blend all of the ingredients in a blender or food processor. Yields about 1 quart.

title: 1 whole chicken with shoes
directions: Mix celery, mushroom soup and chicken soup with the spices. Add carrots, onions and potatoes.
Put chicken whole in a baking bag.
Pour the ingredients over the chicken and seal loosely.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 225° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: sweet lime pickles
directions: Pour water and pickling lime over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours.
Drain off lime water and rinse in cold water unti clear, then cover with ice water.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Cook in mixture 35 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except butter and vanilla, over high heat until boils.
Turn down heat to medium.
Cook approximately 20 minutes or medium ball (dropped in cold water).
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat.
Pour onto buttered meat platter or large plate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add flour and stir.
Melt bouillon in water.
Add to onion mixture.
Add some of hot mixture to sour cream, then stir sour cream into rest of hot mixture.
Combine 1 cup sauce with 1 cup cheese and chicken.
Dip tortillas into remaining sauce in pan, fill with equal portions of chicken mixture, roll up, arrange in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over rolls.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Drain broccoli. Saute onion in oleo. Add broccoli and cook until tender. Add Cheez Whiz to hot rice.
Mix in mushroom soup, celery soup, salt and broccoli.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter or margarine with extract.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add beaten eggs.
Blend in chopped pecans along with syrup and salt.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Take out of oven.
Arrange pecan halves on top of pie.
Return to oven.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until set; cool.
When cut, you may put whipped cream on each piece.

title: chocolate coffee cake
directions: Prepare a chocolate cake box mix as directed and put in a rectangular pan. Mix coffee, brown sugar and cocoa powder together. Drizzle over cake mix. Bake as directed on package.

title: party burgers
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Brown beef and onion until done. Add beans, salt and chili sauce and blend and heat.
Spoon onto toasted buns.

title: apple pizza
directions: Put applesauce and cinnamon/nutmeg on English muffin. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Eat.

title: bo's chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil, then add to flour mixture.
Cream sugar, flour, salt and soda well.
Add sour cream and eggs.
Mix well and pour into greased cookie sheet (18 x 12 x 7/8-inch).
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Ice at once.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Wash meat and place in a large kettle.
Add large can of shredded sauerkraut and enough water to cover meat and kraut. Season with salt and pepper.
Add 2 onions which have been chopped and sauteed in butter.
Cook, covered, slowly until meat is tender, then add roux.

title: winter soup
directions: Add quartered onion, salt, pepper and beef to the 2 quarts of water; bring to a boil and lower heat; simmer 2 hours.
Remove beef; strain stock.
Measure.
Add water to make 2 1/2 quarts. Dice beef. Heat oil in skillet; add sliced onion, garlic, parsley and celery.
Cook 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Return diced beef to stock.
Add contents of skillet, cabbage, carrots and tomatoes.
Cover; simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Add kidney beans, oregano and pastina.
Cook 15 minutes or until the pastina is tender.
Stir in cheese.
Mix well.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients (except the tomato sauce) thoroughly. Put into loaf pan and cover with 2 strips of bacon. Pour the tomato sauce over all. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: layered banana split dessert
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, melted margarine, sugar and pecans.
Press into the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Heat butter and garlic in skillet on medium heat until garlic is lightly browned.
Add crabmeat, half and half and pepper.
Heat about 3 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese.
Stir for one minute.
Serve over cooked fettucini.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese. Garnish with a sprinkle of parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and dried beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 12 slices of dried beef.
Wrap bacon around chicken lengthwise.
Place in dish.
Slice remaining beef in thin strips and sprinkle over chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream together. Spread over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mock oysters
directions: Mix corn, eggs, salt and pepper together, blending well.
Add cracker crumbs and mix thoroughly.
Let rest in refrigerator 1 hour. Form patties 2 1/2-inches in diameter by 1/2-inch in thickness.
In a cast-iron skillet, pan-fry patties slowly in butter until brown and crisp.
Makes 24 patties.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs; beat until fluffy.
In another bowl, combine flour and baking soda.
Add slowly to shortening mixture and mix well.
Add M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or golden brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, starting with dry ingredients and folding oil, apples, pecans and salt into dry.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together cranberry sauce, sugar and pineapple and add nuts and bananas.
Then mix and add Cool Whip.
Place in oblong pan and freeze; cut into squares.

title: apricot wafer dessert
directions: Bring 1/2 cup butter and eggs to room temperature.
Place apricots in medium pan and add water to 1 inch above fruit. Bring to a boil.
Simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain. Sieve to make a puree.
Stir in sugar.
Set aside.

title: ceramic salt dough
directions: Mix ingredients and heat slowly.

title: jellied cranberry mold
directions: In a small bowl sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup water to soften. Chop washed cranberries coarsely.

title: humus
directions: Chop garlic in food processor.
Add beans, processing 1 minute. Scrape bowl. With processor running, slowly pour in 1/2 cup olive oil. Add lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
If mixture is too thick, add more olive oil. Spread on toasted pita wedges or crackers.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.

title: sausage breakfast bake
directions: Combine pancake mix, milk, eggs and oil; beat until nearly smooth with rotary beater.
Turn into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drain apple rings, reserving juice.
Halve each sausage link crosswise.
Arrange apple rings and sausages atop batter in a pattern so the mixture can be cut into squares when baked.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into 6 squares.
Serve with apple-maple syrup.
Serves 6.

title: italian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for an hour or more in sealed plastic bag in refrigerator, turning and mixing once in a while.
Bake, grill, microwave, etc. as usual.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and lemon rind.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to dry mixture.
Add eggs and milk.
Let rise in greased bowl.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes.
Separate bread into small balls, enough to fit muffin tin.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Mix cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
Dip top of rolls in cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples and combine with 3 tablespoons sugar.
In another bowl, sift flour and measure out 3 cups.
Add sugar, salt and powder.
Stir in eggs, oil, juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add apples and cinnamon.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese filling.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Heat pan to 300°.
Saute onion in small amount of butter or oil. Add chicken broth, half and half and cabbage. Stir regularly. Cook 20 minutes until done. Serves 6 to 8.

title: saturday night casserole
directions: Prepare noodles as directed for casserole.
In small saucepan, combine soup and milk until smooth.
Add onion, mustard and sour cream.
Mix well with noodles and ham chunks.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: fraspannkakor(swedish crisp pancakes)
directions: In a medium bowl, beat egg yolks, water, salt, sugar and flour until well blended. Fold in whipped cream. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Rub a crepe pan or small skillet lightly with margarine. Add 3 to 4 tablespoons batter.
Tip pan and let batter spread over bottom. Cook over medium heat just until bubbles appear on surface. Turn and cook until browned. Serve with pureed fruit, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: i-ya(pumpkin)
directions: Cut ripe pumpkin rings; remove the peeling.
Hang on a stick before the fire, near enough to dry slowly.
This may be stored until ready for use.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Drop biscuits into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place biscuits in Bundt pan.
Melt margarine.
Pour margarine and honey or Karo syrup into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Cook peas until done.
Drain well. Cook the ground beef until almost done.
Place a layer of peas in casserole dish, followed by a layer of ground beef and a layer of onions.
Put ketchup on top of onions.
Repeat the layers, ending with ketchup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled cocktail shrimp
directions: In a large bowl, mix shrimp and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil and pour over shrimp. Refrigerate and allow to marinate several days, stirring several times each day.
When ready to serve, remove shrimp with slotted spoon and serve with toothpicks.
Makes about 30 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add nuts and carrots.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburgers, indian style
directions: Mix the ground lamb and salt thoroughly.
Form into 2-inch diameter meat patties and brown in olive oil until a rich deep brown.
Turn down heat and add onions, all spices and tomatoes. Simmer for 45 minutes.
Cover; stir during this time.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl, combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg at low speed until stiff dough forms.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine until tender.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Melt soup with cheese in saucepan.
Add mushrooms and juice and bread crumbs; mix well.
Mix all ingredients except onion rings
and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°. Remove lid; sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add more water if needed.

title: carrot bars
directions: Combine ingredients in that order.
Place in a jelly roll pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Spread with cream cheese frosting.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, pineapple juice, water and sugar.
Blend in sherbet and pour ginger ale over it just before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn off cobs.
Grind cabbage, onions, peppers and celery.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in small amount of cooking oil.
Add green beans and tomatoes until boiling.
Reduce heat.
Add seasonings and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery with a little water in microwave for 2 minutes, until tender.
Combine with the rest of ingredients and spread in casserole.
Top with 1 cup crushed Ritz crackers, 2 tablespoons almonds and 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: parsnip cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add eggs, vanilla, oil, parsnips and cinnamon.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
A cream cheese frosting may be used.

title: dorman's baked beans
directions: Boil
beans
approximately 20 minutes (or set overnight in water
to
swell).	Use same water beans swelled in and put in bean
pot
with
beans
about
inches from top rim.
Add onion, molasses,	honey,	brown
sugar,
salt pork and 3 or 4 dashes of dry mustard.
Cover pot and bake at 250° for 8 to 9 hours.	Check often to see if water needs to be added.

title: "apple tortilla dessert"
directions: Put apples in tortillas.
Put in 13 x 9 pan.
Mix milk and sugar; add melted margarine.
Pour over tortillas; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Let sit 1 hour.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
You may use any pie filling.

title: speedy pasta with chicken
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken, onion and garlic.
Cook until chicken and onion are tender.
Stir in sauce. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, stirring frequently for 10 minutes.

title: my favorite chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper in a shallow bowl.
Melt butter and garlic in pan over low heat.
Dip chicken pieces in garlic butter, then cover with crumbs. Arrange in shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: avocado, tomato and onion salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Serve as a side dish or with a crusty bread.

title: no-boil classic lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and eggs. Mix well. In 13 x 9-inch pan, spread 1 cup pasta sauce. Layer with half each of the uncooked lasagna noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture, sausage, remaining pasta sauce and Mozzarella. Repeat layering. Top with parsley. Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake 1 hour. Uncover. Bake an additional 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Let stand 15 minutes and serve. Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, onion and sour cream together. Spray long dish with Pam.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and golden.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Arrange chicken in bottom of baking dish. Mix broth, soup and English peas and carrots. Pour over chicken. Melt butter. Add flour and milk; mix well (batter will be thin). Pour over top; do not stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: loving cup punch
directions: Using large pitcher, reconstitute lemonade according to directions on can.
Add cranberry juice cocktail and enough ice to chill.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Makes 10 to 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Beat 2 eggs in a bowl and add 1/2 pint sour cream and 1 teaspoon soda.
Beat well and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake in greased 15 x 1 x 1-inch pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch for 28 minutes at 375°.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers and bananas in 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix pudding according to package directions and immediately pour over wafers and bananas. Let set for a few minutes until pudding begins to thicken. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, fry sausage until cooked.
Remove sausage; drain on paper towel.
Reserve 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onion and green pepper in reserved fat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Slice sausage.

title: pineapple sundae sauce
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir undrained pineapple, brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in milk, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes until starting to boil.
Stir in butter.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes until clear and no starchy taste remains.

title: ali's oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Combine 1 1/2 cups of flour, baking soda and salt. Stir into the shortening mixture.
Stir in oatmeal.
Stir in nuts. Toss apricots and remaining 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir into dough. Stir in white chocolate chips.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Flatten slightly and place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes until slightly moist in the center and just beginning to brown around the edges.
Remove immediately to wax paper-covered paper towels.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Form into balls and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: beef stuffed peppers(basic recipe makes 4 servings)
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise; remove seeds and membranes. Cook peppers, covered, in 1-inch boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Brown beef and onion in skillet 5 minutes.
Add rice, salt, pepper, 1 can tomato sauce and corn.
Bring to boiling, about 3 minutes.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: apple crisp(6 servings)
directions: Place apples in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In a small mixing bowl, microwave butter at High for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 minutes, or until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples, then press down lightly.
Microwave at High for 8 minutes.
Rotate dish one-half turn.
Microwave at High for 6 to 10 minutes more, or until apples are tender.
Serve warm, cold, plain or topped with whipped cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix eggs, butter, sour cream and cornbread mix in a large bowl.
Add corn and stir thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish, filling to 1/2-inch below rim.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
For reduce calories, omit sour cream.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix together.
Chill 15 to 30 minutes.
Press into small muffin tins.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Sift flour and mix with salt and spices.
Set aside.
Cream sugars, eggs and oil.
Beat the buttermilk and soda well by hand. Add to creamed mixture. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Mix and bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix spices and oil. Add crackers and mix. Ready to serve.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs and remove shells.
Heat vinegar, sugar, salt and beet juice until sugar is dissolved.
Add beets and eggs. Prepare a couple of days ahead and store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in flour and nuts.
Press into deep pie pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Arrange broccoli in large baking pan.
Place chicken on top. Combine in pan soup, mayo and thyme and pour over chicken. Sprinkle on cheese.
Combine soft bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Recipe can be halved.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper together.
Drain off grease.
Add oregano, garlic powder, sage and tomato sauce. Cook for 10 minutes, then add rice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with pudding.
Let stand until thick. Add most of container of Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Best if made the night before.

title: fusilli with pesto
directions: For pesto, in a blender container or food processor bowl combine basil, parsley, Parmesan or Romano cheese, oil, nuts, garlic and salt.
Cover and blend or process with several on-off turns until a paste form, stopping the machine several times and scraping the sides.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Beat eggs; add fruit cocktail and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot peppers canned in catsup
directions: Cook all ingredients together until almost boiling or peppers color changes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pudding cake
directions: Combine and mix all except pudding mix.
Mix until smooth. Add pudding mix and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes approximately 24 cupcakes.

title: tuna casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1/2 pound of Velveeta cheese (cubed).
Stir until melted.
Add macaroni, peas, tuna and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with cheese slices (cut in triangles).
Continue baking until cheese melts.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Drain shrimp well.
Mince green onions.
Blend together the softened cream cheese and oleo.
Mix in mayonnaise, shrimp and onions.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic salt and Tabasco sauce; mix well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Season with salt and pepper and add enough gravy to cover.
Cook over low heat four weeks, stirring constantly. Serves about 3,000 people.
If more are expected, add the rabbits. However, do this only if necessary since most people do not like hares in their stew.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted boiling water.
Brown sausage; drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Pour drippings in saucepan; add onion and green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cream style corn; mix well. Add cheese to sauce.
Remove from heat; rinse macaroni.
Put one layer of sausage into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with layer of macaroni, then repeat layers.
Pour sauce over casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs and paprika.
Bake in 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
After chicken is boiled and tender, take the skin off and debone the chicken; save broth.
Mix corn bread and crackers and boil eggs; chop and add to corn bread and crackers.
Saute onion, celery and peppers and add to corn bread mixture.
Now mix altogether with broth.
Add enough water to make juicy.
You don't want it dry.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. If desired, serve with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high 5 minutes.
Beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix together all dry ingredients and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Spread mixture onto pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn onto towel covered with powdered sugar.
Roll in towel. Chill.

title: mama's cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
If you like sweet cornbread, include the sugar (I omit this).
Add the eggs, milk and vegetable oil to the dry ingredients.
Use a seasoned black iron skillet for best results.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons oil or bacon drippings to pan and place in oven to heat.
When a drop of water sizzles (pan shouldn't be smoking), remove from oven and add batter.
Batter should sizzle some as you add it.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; turn out onto plate.
Enjoy!

title: three bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Bring all ingredients except spaghetti and zucchini to boil. Add spaghetti and reduce heat.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Add zucchini and simmer for additional 15 minutes.
Pour in bowls and sprinkle with cheese.

title: seafood shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter for three minutes.
Stir in flour.
Cook one minute.
Add all liquids and stir constantly for five minutes.
Add seasonings, pimento, and shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, milk, oil and cereal.
Stir to break up cereal.
Mix in apple, brown sugar and nuts.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Turn into pan.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes until tester comes out clean.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing from pan. Makes 1 loaf.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise, leaving 1/8-inch shell.
Remove potato from hull.
Combine potatoes, 1 cup cheese, Miracle Whip, milk, egg and seasonings.
Beat until fluffy.
Refill potato shells with mixture.
Top with remaining cheese, onions and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.

title: the ultimate sugar cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar and Crisco in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix until well blended.
Divide dough into quarters.
Wrap and chill for 1 hour.
Spread 1 tablespoon of flour on a sheet of waxed paper. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out with floured cutter. Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Don't overbake!!!

title: homemade yogurt in a thermos
directions: Fill Thermos with very hot water; set aside.
Heat milk to temperature of 95° to 115° (use cooking thermometer as this temperature is very important:
too
low
sours; too high -kills).
Pour into bowl
and
add milk powder and yogurt;	mix well.
(Add optional
gelatin at this point).
Pour water from thermos and fill with yogurt mixture.
Tightly cap lid and set aside; note time.
After 3 hours, you should have thin yogurt; after 6 hours,
thick
yogurt.
Pour
small
amount first into small jar to use
as a starter next time.
Pour remainder into container and refrigerate.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Cook large pieces or whole cauliflower for 12 to 15 minutes in boiling, salted water; drain well.
Place in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with salt.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard; spread over. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6. (Could cut it up as well.)

title: easy lime pie
directions: Mix condensed milk well with limeade.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Chill for 6 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour the dressing over all.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: peanut butter pies
directions: Bake pie shell and let cool.

title: holiday ice cream fruit punch
directions: Mix punch as directed.
Just before serving, add scoops of sherbet and soft drink.
Soft drink will make the sherbet foam. This makes a beautiful holiday drink when you add a frozen ring with cherries in it.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Sift flour. Measure and sift again soda, salt and cocoa. Cream shortening. Add sugar and egg and beat well. Add flour mixture and milk alternately. Add vanilla. Drop and bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Take out and place 1/2 marshmallow on top. Return to oven for 2 more minutes. Take out and spread marshmallow over top of cookie with finger. Ice with chocolate powdered sugar icing.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix flour and
1/2 c. sugar. Add shortening, salt and baking powder. Stir in milk. Pour mixture into cake pan. Layer sliced apples over mixture. Add 3/4 c. sugar and cinnamon. Bake 350 degrees
till golden brown. Beat egg. Blend in
cream and 1 Tbsp. sugar. With fork spread on cake when nearly done. Put back in oven for another 10 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add a few drops of yellow food coloring.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Fast and easy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
On low speed, beat sugar, margarine and eggs until just blended.
Increase to high speed until light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
Reduce speed to low and add bananas and 1/4 cup water.
Beat until well mixed. Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat until blended.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Test with toothpick in center and comes out clean.

title: banana pepper casserole
directions: Place peppers (cleaned, deseeded and halved) in bottom of casserole dish.
Saute beef in separate skillet; drain.
Pour over peppers.
Mix water and flour to make a thin white sauce and pour over peppers and beef.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cut kraut with scissors or a knife.
Combine kraut, onion, celery, green pepper and carrot.
Heat sugar and vinegar to boiling point.
Pour over mixture.
Cover bowl tightly and let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: french bread spread
directions: Cream all ingredients together; spread in bread which has been sliced lengthwise and hollowed out.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, or until cheese melts.
Slice and serve hot.

title: amish marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm. Makes 2 1/4 pounds.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Slowly melt caramels and 1/3 cup Pet milk; set aside.
Melt butter and add to cake mix.
Add 1/3 cup Pet milk to cake and butter mixture.
Pat into pan.
Cook for 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Then pour caramel mixture and pecans.
Cook 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting. Store in a cool place.

title: wacky cake
directions: Use an ungreased 8-inch cake pan.
Sift together flour, sugar, soda and cocoa.
You can put these dry ingredients in your ungreased pan.
Make 3 wells in the flour mixture.
Put 1 teaspoon vanilla in the first, 1 teaspoon vinegar in the second and 6 tablespoons melted oleo in the third.
Pour 1 cup water over all and mix with a fork until ingredients are entirely moist.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, evaporated milk, raw rice, onion and 1 teaspoon salt in a bowl.
With wet hands, shape meat mixture into 8 balls.
Put balls into skillet, about 1/2 inch apart.
Then mix tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt and water.
Save 3/4 of this mixture for sauce.
Pour rest over meatballs.
Bring to boil, then cover tightly and cook over low heat 45 minutes.
Turn meatballs twice while cooking.
When meatballs are done, remove from skillet.
Pour saved mixture into skillet and heat until steaming hot.
Serve sauce with meatballs.
Serves 4.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chips over medium heat.
Gradually add evaporated milk, then powdered sugar and vanilla.
Bring to boil; boil about 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit cream of tartar, soda and salt.

title: forever ambers
directions: Mix all and pour in jelly roll pan. Bake at 300° until set in middle about 30 to 40 minutes. Roll by teaspoonful in powdered sugar.

title: strawberry icebox pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cherry jello, frozen strawberries and juice of 1 lemon. Put over low flame and stir until jello dissolves. Cool the ingredients. Whip chilled milk. Mix with jello, strawberries, lemon juice and sugar. Beat up thoroughly and pour into 2 baked pie shells and sit in icebox.

title: coating mix for chicken
directions: Mix together flour, spices and salt in a sealable plastic bag. When ready to prepare chicken, beat together buttermilk and eggs. Dip chicken in buttermilk mixture and then in the plastic bag of dry ingredients.
Shake until chicken is well coated.
Chicken is now ready to fry, bake, broil or grill as desired.

title: whiting hawaiian punch
directions: Chill all ingredients before mixing.
Decorate with umbrellas and cherries and pineapple chunks.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and thoroughly drain spinach.
Mix spinach and remaining ingredients well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with variety of fresh vegetables.

title: black forest torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush sides and bottoms of 4 (9-inch) round layer pans with margarine.

Bake only 2 layers at a time. Measure into large mixing bowl all cake ingredients except eggs. Beat at low speed to blend, then beat at medium speed 2 minutes, scraping sides and bottom of bowl frequently.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more.
Pour 1/4 batter (or 1 cup) into each pan.
Layers will be thin.

title: praline glaze
directions: Bake ham according to package directions. Spread glaze over ham approximately 20 to 30 minutes before ham is done and continue baking.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine and put into baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pat stuffing on bottom of casserole dish (sprayed with Pam first), then put cut up chicken on top.
Put one can of chicken soup on top (no water).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Break bread into small pieces and place in well-greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cut cheese into cubes; sprinkle over bread. Sprinkle meat over cheese and pour margarine over meat.
Beat eggs with mustard, salt and milk, then pour over casserole.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break lettuce up, then slice thinly 1 onion and cut 1 head of cauliflower into small pieces.
Arrange in layers.
Then cook bacon; crumble and place as next layer.
Mix cheese and sugar and sprinkle over bacon.
Frost with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Toss 20 minutes before serving.

title: easy fruit pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lay out crescent rolls on baking sheet wide ends together, points out.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolk, and zest.
Spread down middle of crescent rolls.
Spread pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Fold points over filling, meeting in the middle.
Bake at 375° 25-30 minutes; mix lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Drizzle over pastry.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix sugar, salt and vinegar together.
Boil this together; let cool.
Pour mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Let stand in refrigerator for 12 hours, then put in containers and freeze.
A good way to use surplus cukes.
I have done this and they are really quite good.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add all other ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into 2 to 3 greased and floured 13 ounce coffee cans.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: lemon-herbed turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
With a fork, prick surface of lemon. Place in cavity of turkey breast along with fresh herbs.
Place flour in oven cooking bag and shake.
Place prepared turkey breast in bag.
Close bag securely.
Make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top of bag to allow steam to escape.
Place in a shallow pan large enough to hold turkey breast comfortably.
Roast at 325° for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until a meat thermometer placed in thickest muscle, without touching a bone, reaches 170°.
If fresh herbs are unavailable, use 1/4 teaspoon each of dried herbs.

title: pepperoni buns
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 1/2 c. flour, yeast, sugar and salt. In sauce pan, heat water, milk and shortening about 125°.
Add to flour mixture and beat for 3 minutes by hand.
Use the rest of the flour to make a firm dough, knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 minutes.
Divide dough into 20 equal parts, shape into balls. Place on greased sheet pans.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise until double.
Pull dough balls to 5 inch lengths.
Roll 2 sticks of pepperoni in each roll so they do not touch, place on pans. Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 425° for about 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 20 buns.
In Memory of Blanch and Bob Herron.

title: bread and butter pickles(from kerr)
directions: Thoroughly wash cucumbers and remove 1/8 inch from the blossom end.
Slice all cucumbers into 1/4-inch slices.
Wash peppers and cut in half.
Remove seeds and cut peppers into 1-inch size squares.
Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain, rinse and drain.
In a 10-quart saucepan, combine vinegar, mustard seed, sugar and turmeric.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumber mixture.
Warm thoroughly but do not boil. Immediately fill hot pint jar with mixture, leaving 1/2 inch space at top. Run a non-metal spoon down through the jar to remove bubbles.
Wipe jar tops clean and place on hot lids.
Screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Makes 14 pints.

title: mints
directions: Blend cream cheese and flavoring with fork.
Add food coloring until it is color you desire.
Blend in powdered sugar until mixture is consistency of pie dough.
Form into balls and mash with a fork.

title: winter stew
directions: Brown stew beef in hot shortening in a heavy skillet. Sprinkle with seasoned salt as it cooks.
Add boiling water and tomato juice.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Add more water or tomato sauce, if desired. Serve with biscuits.
Really good for cold days.

title: stelline's unexpected company cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, cherry juice and eggs.
Stir until all lumps are dissolved.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Fold in cherries.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 11 1/2-inch Pyrex oblong dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: butternut cake with frosting
directions: Cream shortening and sugar for 2 minutes at high speed.
Add flour and milk alternately, adding flour last.
Blend well.
Put in a cold oven and bake 1 hour at 325°, then bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 250°.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: custard bread pudding(very good)
directions: Scald milk and pour over bread crumbs, cool.
Add melted butter, sugar, eggs, salt and spice.
Pour into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: southern comfort sausage cake(in honor of princess patty)
directions: Bring the raisins and the water to a boil before adding to the other ingredients.
Stir or mix with hands the sausage and light brown sugar together.
Add the boiled raisins and water.
Mix all the dry ingredients together and add to the sausage-raisins mixture alternately with the Southern Comfort.
Then add the nuts. Stir all well and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex baking dish, or in a Bundt pan, well-greased and bake 1 hour (more or less) in a 375° preheated oven.
When cake is done and cooled for perhaps 10 minutes one can pour a glaze over.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fry bacon strips until crispy.
Remove from grease and crush bacon into small pieces.
In a pan on the stove, cook the cream of onion soup.
Add crushed bacon pieces; gradually add Velveeta cheese.
Continuously stir on medium-low heat until Velveeta cheese has melted.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain water.
Place broccoli into a large casserole dish.
Pour mixture onto broccoli.
Cover with onion rings.
Preheat oven to 325°. Bake casserole for 30 minutes.
Serves approximately 8 to 10.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients into a bowl and stir together. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: pudding delight
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with graham crackers.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package for pudding.
Spread half pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Add remaining pudding mixture.
Add remaining crackers.
Spread cherry pie filling over crackers.
Chill 3 hours.
Serves 9.

title: kenny's cupcakes
directions: *Pistachio is great for St. Patrick's Day!

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix well.
Use hand beater to make salad smooth.
Put in flat bowl and chill overnight.

title: fillets in lemon butter(microwave)
directions: In 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish, arrange fillets with thickest part to outside edge of dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done (let cool).
Fry bacon until crisp. Take out and drain.
Pour off half the grease.
Leave rest in skillet.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Grate onion fine on potatoes and mix.
Keep on warm burner until ready to serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, add tomato paste, stewed tomatoes and garlic salt.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs and parsley.
Cook noodles as package directs.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and 1/2 meat sauce; repeat layers.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.
Can be made ahead and later baked.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Blend well with mixer.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Cool; roll again.

title: maple oatmeal bread(may be used in a bread machine.)
directions: Put all the ingredients into the pan in the order listed. Select white bread and push to start or manual method. Mix together and knead; let this rise and knead a second time.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans; let rise. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix ingredients. Dip chicken in mixture. Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate mint ribbon cake
directions: Make cake.
Coat 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan with no stick cooking spray.
Line with waxed paper.
Coat with cooking spray.
Spread cake batter in pan.
Bake at 350 degrees 25 - 30 minutes or until center springs back.
Let cool in pan 30 minutes then invert onto waxed paper.
Cool completely.

title: pasta fazul
directions: Cook lima beans until almost done; add spaghetti sauce.
Mix well, then saute onion to golden brown.
Add together with all other ingredients; cook until beans are done.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg; mix well. Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of pan. Bake 10 minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1 can of shrimp.
Use mixer or food processor.
Blend until smooth or fluffy.
Fold second can of shrimp in gently.
May be molded or served in a bowl with assorted crackers.

title: ice cream without a freezer
directions: Crush 1 roll of cookies and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ice cream on top of the cookies.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Put the pan in the freezer to re-freeze.
Just before serving, sprinkle the top with more crushed cookies.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange crinkles
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well, drop from tsp onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10-20 min. until golden. Cool on cookie sheet about 1-5 min then remove.
Yield 4-5 doz cookies.

title: super seafood salad
directions: Cut crab flakes in half; combine with rest of ingredients. Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: soyameat and croutons
directions: Make white sauce of margarine, flour, salt and Mocha Mix. Blend diced soyameat chicken style into mixture.
Drain asparagus and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place asparagus in bottom of a large flat buttered baking dish.
Pour white sauce mixture over asparagus.
Toss croutons with melted margarine and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Separate eggs.

title: golden's chicken tetrazzini
directions: In greased casserole, layer macaroni, layer chicken and layer of mushrooms.
Mix soup and evaporated milk and pour over layered ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a large baking dish with vegetable oil.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Turn into prepared baking dish; cover and bake for 45 minutes.

title: chilled strawberry soup
directions: In Blender, mix together equal amounts of buttermilk and fresh strawberries. Sweeten to taste with sugar or honey.
Chill a few hours. Top with fruit and a sprig of mint.

title: applesauce cake deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan and set aside.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Bring water with cobs to a boil for 10 minutes.
Measure 3 cups liquid and strain through cloth.
Put into saucepan.
Add box of fruit pectin.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil; add 4 cups sugar and bring to simmer for 3 minutes, then skim.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Pour into glasses and seal.
Jelly will be clear and taste like honey.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Cut turnips and carrots into very thin slices.
Add 1/3 tablespoon salt and mix well.
Let stand 30 minutes, then press excess liquid out.
Add 1/4 cup water and 2 tablespoons vinegar and allow them to stand for 30 minutes.

title: chuck roast
directions: Put tenderizer on both sides of roast.
Marinate in juice for 24 hours.
Cook 40 to 60 minutes depending on doneness desired. This is to be cooked on grill.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add flour and cream gradually. Add vanilla. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in Bundt pan. Cool upright 45 minutes and then invert on plate.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over low heat 3 to 4 hours, or cook overnight in a crock-pot.

title: salami
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Wrap in a 12 x 14-inch size sheet of foil, shiny side out.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of foil and place on rack of oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: fried pies
directions: Cut Crisco into flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and egg.
Work together well, then chill in refrigerator. Will keep for 2 weeks.
Pinch off piece the size of a walnut and roll out.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Blend with spoon.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Place Tater Tots over top. Crush cereal over top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: triple beef and bean casserole
directions: Cut bacon into bits; fry and drain.
Fry ground beef and chopped onion until brown; drain off excess grease.
Combine with other ingredients; place in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Mix together drained pineapple, apples, celery and nuts.
In saucepan, mix eggs, sugar, lemon juice, salt and pineapple juice. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until slightly thickened. Cool.
In chilled bowl, beat whipppig cream until piles softly. Fold into cooled egg mixture.
Pour over fruit mixture and toss slightly.
Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and freeze.
Allow salad to slightly thaw for serving.

title: doughnuts
directions: Heat milk slightly and dissolve yeast.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Cream shortening, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Blend this mixture into yeast sponge.
Add remaining flour and knead well, about 5 minutes.
Rub with shortening and let rise again until double in bulk.
Roll about 1/2-inch thick and cut with doughnut cutter.
Let rise about 45 minutes.
Fry in deep shortening.
Dip in caramel syrup.
Let cool.

title: jello salad
directions: Blend in dry jello with cottage cheese.
Add pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: easy skillet dinner
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet. Drain all grease.
Add mushrooms, noodles and cabbage.
Cook on medium-low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry and cranberry salad
directions: Add water to Jell-O and mix well. Immediately add strawberries and mix well.
When cool, add cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until well set. Cream the cheese. Add the mayonnaise and Cool Whip and spread over Jell-O.

title: baked chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Cream together oleo and the sugar.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Then add nuts.
Pour into ungreased pan.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except dinner rolls and melted butter.
Split the dinner rolls and butter both sides.
Spread with ham and cheese mixture.
Place halves back together and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: peach bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add peach puree (can use baby food peaches) and dry ingredients. Mix well.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour half in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: italian chicken
directions: Combine dressing mix, juice and oil.
Pour over chicken in casserole dish.
Marinate for 6 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: cherry pie
directions: Dissolve jello, cinnamon and sugar in boiling water.
Drain cherries, measuring 1/2 cup of the syrup.
Stir into gelatin. Chill until very thick.
Then add cherries and nuts.
Pour into pastry shell.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with prepared Dream Whip or whipped cream, if desired.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and flavorings until smooth.
Blend in 2 tablespoons sugar, flour and pecans.
Roll into small balls and place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate morsels, peanut
butter and margarine. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal and stir until well coated. Pour powdered sugar in plastic bag.
Put coated cereal in sack and shake well until coated.
Pour on flat pan to cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix and bake in 3 layers at 350° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Pour in casserole dish after mixing.
Mix first 4 ingredients. Mix margarine (melted) and Pepperidge Farm dressing mix and put on top of casserole.
Cook in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: talerine
directions: Saute beef and onion until brown.
Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients to beef and onion.
Heat in oven at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: jalapeno-cheese cornbread
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add cheese and jalapeno, mixing well.

title: beer batter for fish or vegetables
directions: Combine all dry ingredients. Stir beaten egg into beer.
Add to dry ingredients. Batter will thicken as it sets.
Add more beer if it is needed. Batter can be stored in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days. Recipe can be doubled.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix sugar and margarine together; add flour and eggs (one at a time).
Add milk to mixture, along with vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Lower to 325° and cook 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Done when toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: french potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, covered, in enough boiling salted water to cover for 30 minutes, or just until fork-tender.
Drain, peel and slice while still warm into 1/4-inch thick slices into salad bowl. In bowl or jar with tight fitting lid, combine vinegar and rest of ingredients; mix very well.
Pour over warm potatoes, gently, to coat with liquid.
Serve warm or let cool and refrigerate. Before serving, toss gently again.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scrapple
directions: Mix meal, flour and hot sauce in 1/2 of cold stock.
Bring 1/2 stock to boiling.
Slowly stir in corn meal mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Continue cooking for 30 minutes.
Stir in sausage.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Cool and refrigerate. When firm, cut into slices.
Roll in flour and fry in oil until brown on both sides.
Serve with syrup.

title: molded holiday cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Chop up to separate berries.
Drain and add crushed pineapple.
Pour half of this mixture in a large mold and congeal.
Soften and whip cream cheese and a small amount of mayonnaise with a mixer until spreadable.
Add pecan pieces to cream cheese and spread on congealed half of salad.
Pour remainder of cranberry jello mixture on top of cream cheese layer and congeal.
Unmold salad with cream cheese center for a beautiful and delicious holiday salad.
Guests always ask for this recipe!

title: shortbread-butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients with hands; roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until light golden brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Decorate with colored sugars, etc., before baking or icing after baking.
Also delicious plain.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat butter over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables. Reserve.
Prepare Pastry (recipe follows).

title: holiday poke cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare, bake and cool cake as directed on package for 2 (9-inch) round cake layers.
Place cake layers, top sides up, in clean, 9-inch, round cake pans.
Poke cake with large fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Stir 1 cup of the boiling water into each flavor of gelatin in separate bowls for 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Carefully pour red gelatin over 1 cake layer and the lime gelatin over second cake layer.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix by following directions on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake according to directions.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook
until
mixture coats spoon. Cool. Pour into can and fill with milk.
Freeze.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add oil and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, cream of tartar, vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Mix well. Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press with a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 13 to 14 dozen.
You can add 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans and a dash of nutmeg if desired.

title: baked apples microwave
directions: Put apples in a 1-quart Pyrex casserole dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar, butter slices and dash of cinnamon.
Cover and cook in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes (until apples are tender). Stir once during cook time.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Put oleo into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and set in oven at 350° until melted. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Spoon chicken mixture into center.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Put 4 cups sweet potatoes in
a greased casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients well, and
pour over sweet potatoes. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes
or until sticky.
Cover the top with small marshmallows and brown lightly until they begin to melt.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Chop well with knife and fork.
Form into crust in 2 buttered 10-inch pie tins or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cook ground chuck and onion (drain off fat).
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, sugar, water and seasonings.
Heat through.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoon and let cool.

title: tuna-nut stuffed pasta shells
directions: In saucepan, saute garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, honey, oregano, salt, basil and pepper; cook for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: polish sausage dinner
directions: Slice Polish sausage into 1-inch slices.
Brown slightly in a large pot.
Cover with Bavarian sauerkraut.
Add sliced vegetables on top of kraut.
Cook on low heat until potatoes and carrots are done.

title: shrimp tempura batter
directions: Combine flour, cornstarch, baking powder and baking soda in a bowl.
Add salt, egg and water; stir until flour is moistened. Batter should be slightly lumpy.
Dip shrimp in batter.
May also be used with broccoli and sweet potatoes.

title: pecan cream cheese bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and 1/4 cup chopped pecans.
Beat until combined.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Pat into ungreased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Cream together 2 eggs, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle remaining pecans over mixture. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting into bars.

title: ginger chicken with peaches
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Cook chicken in a 10-inch skillet in hot margarine over medium heat about 10 minutes or until tender enough to easily pierce with fork.
Remove from skillet; cover to keep warm.
Drain peaches, keeping the syrup.
Add water to the syrup to make 3/4 cup total.
Blend with the cornstarch and ginger root.
Add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add peaches and water chestnuts and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spoon over chicken; serve with rice.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Mix salt, ketchup, chili powder, water, dry mustard and brown sugar and set aside.
Place pork chops in greased baking dish and top with lemon and onion slices.
Pour marinade mixture over pork chops and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Bake at 325 degrees covered for 2 hours.
Remove cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Spoon sauce over pork chops.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix raisins and sugar; fill center of apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Place in crock-ette; add 1/2 cup of water.
Cover and cook 7 to 9 hours.

title: shrimp crab salad
directions: Cook,
drain and cool macaroni.
Mix all other ingredients and serve.
You can invite all the neighbors in for this. It makes a bunch!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Bring 1 quart of water to boil.
Add sliced zucchini and boil 5 minutes with the onion after it has returned to boiling.
Drain well in colander.
In separate pan, melt butter and add soup and sour cream.
Stir in both packages of stuffing mix.
Toss in zucchini.
Mix gently.
Place in greased casserole and cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with grated cheese. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface. Sprinkle with sugar.
Cut and bake in 425° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: honey chicken
directions: Shake chicken in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake chicken in pan at 400° for 20 minutes. Add glaze (honey and lemon) for at least 1/2 hour.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In oblong baking dish pour a little spaghetti sauce in dish. Dip chicken in eggs and bread crumbs, then fry in oil.
Dip cooked chicken in spaghetti sauce that is in the dish on both sides and lay chicken in dish.
Put grated cheese on and pour spaghetti sauce on and more cheese.
Make sure sauce is on top and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add fruit juice to jello mixture. Set aside 1 cup of jello mixture to chill and whip later.
Add fruit to mixture and pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Let set.

title: cheese chowder
directions: In a saucepan, combine vegetables. Add 2 cups water and bring to a boil. Simmer for 10 minutes. Do not drain.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Melt butter and oil.
In skillet, cook onion and garlic.
Stir in chicken broth, wine, oregano, dash of pepper and salt to taste and reserved clam liquid.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add clams to sauce to heat through.
Cook linguine; drain.
Add sauce to linguine along with grated cheese and toss.
Garnish with fresh parsley, if desired.

title: machanka for christmas eve mushroom barley soup
directions: Bring 4 cups water to a boil; add barley.
Cook together until barley is done, stirring often and adding water when needed.
Add sauerkraut juice.
Make Zapraska as follows:

title: singapore wings
directions: Marinate chicken 2 to 3 hours in sauce.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Put into crock-pot to keep warm while serving.
Keep turning to keep sauce over them.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Blend together sugar and oil; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add pineapple and juice, carrots, nuts and mix well.
Bake in layer pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mountain cherry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl.
Serve with ice. Yield: 25 servings (4 ounces each).

title: texas ranch cake(servings:  8)
directions: Bake cornbread in three 9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pans.
These cornbread layers should be no more than 1-inch thick.
Select a large skillet and brown the sausage, breaking into ground meat-size morsels.
When sausage is cooked, drain carefully.
Add onion and green bell pepper.
Stir in Ro-Tel tomatoes and slowly simmer, while continuing to stir, until onion and green bell pepper are slightly softened.
Drain and mash pinto beans, then add to sausage mixture.
Continue slowly heating and stirring while adding Velveeta cheese.
Once the cheese is melted, the filler mixture is ready.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish; put cheese on top.
Mix soup and milk; pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing over soup; spoon butter over stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and saute chopped stems in margarine. Add onion, salami, cheese and oregano.
Add crushed crackers. Fill mushroom caps and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: prize brownies
directions: *Can use cocoa. Use 3 tablespoons cocoa plus 1 tablespoon oil for each ounce can be substituted.

title: big boy pie
directions: Take 1 cup water and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add some of the cornstarch, then add the Jell-O and rest of cornstarch to 1/3 cup water.
Add that to the first mixture.
Cook until thick; let cool.
When cool, add berries.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix
the first 3 ingredients well.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Make a well in the dry ingredients; pour the sugar, eggs and oil mixture into sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add applesauce; mix well.
Walnuts are optional.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pizza bake
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix egg, milk and salt; pour over noodles in cake pan.
Cook sausage and ground meat and add sauce, oregano and garlic salt.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook rice separately.
Mix all together in large pan.
Cook until done.
Add cooked rice.
You can eat this like soup.
Good with cornbread.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Fill bowl with lettuce, add onions, spread mayonnaise over. Sprinkle sugar, add cheese, black olives and bacon.
Refrigerate. Mix before serving.

title: fish and broccoli roll-ups
directions: Spread chopped broccoli/cheese mixture over fish fillets. Roll up and place seam side down in greased 11 x 7 inch baking dish. Squeeze lemon juice over all.
Drizzle top with a little oil and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for approximately 30 - 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter patties
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey and dry milk in bowl; mix well. Shape into long thin roll.
Chill until firm.
Cut into slices. Dip each slice in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Yield: 1 pound.

title: carrot and squash
directions: Combine melted oleo and stuffing mix. Put in 2 cups of stuffing mix in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook both kind of sliced squash 6 to 8 minutes. Drain and mash. Mix squash with all the rest of the ingredients. Put it in the baking dish on top of the stuffing mix and put the rest of the stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain well and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut Velveeta cheese in 1/4-inch slices and cover top of broccoli.
Crush 1 tube of crackers and cover cheese.
Melt butter and pour over crackers. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice bacon strips.
Dice onion.
Saute bacon and onion in a saucepan.
Pare and dice potatoes.
Dice celery.
Put potatoes and celery in water to cook.
Add sauteed bacon and onion to mixture, then add egg dumplings, if desired, to cooking mixture.

title: toffee
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 10 x 15-inch jellyroll pan with aluminum foil. Place saltines (7 down, 5 across) in pan. Combine brown sugar and butter and melt and cook on top of stove. (If doing in the microwave, can be very tricky...needs to melt and cook a few minutes.) Stir thoroughly and pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 15 to 16 minutes. Remove from oven and cover with chocolate chips. When chips melt, smooth over with spatula and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Chill for 1 hour. Break into bite size pieces. Refrigerate in tin.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Reduced fat items can be substituted, also mushrooms can be used.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Cook pudding and juice to boil.
Set aside and let cool.
Combine fruit in bowl.
Pour pudding over fruit.
Mix together.
Refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the four ingredients together. Chill until slightly congealed. Whip in 1 cup of sour cream and 1 cup of pecans. Refrigerate until thick.

title: homemade caramel corn
directions: Remove any unpopped kernels of corn.
Add peanuts, set aside. Bring brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt to boil.
boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat, quickly add baking soda.
Gently mix with the popcorn.
Divide popcorn mixture equally into 2 buttered 9 x 9-inch square cake pans.
Cook at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove and spread it out on waxed paper to cool.

title: doughnuts
directions: Let first 3 ingredients rise.
Sift flour and melt oleo.
Mix beaten eggs with yeast.
Let rise.
When rinse, knead and let rise a second time.
Roll out and cut with glass.
Let rise a couple minutes and fry in hot Crisco.
Done when fork comes out clean.

title: elizabeth's dessert bars
directions: Combine cake mix, brown sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: shoestring hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat.
Blend soup and milk.
Mix everything in 4-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover last 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: noodles-n-pork
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and set aside.
Cook and drain pork.
In large saucepan, pour in all ketchup.
Fill the bottle with water and pour in with ketchup.
Add sugar; stir well and let simmer 20 minutes.
Add pork the last 5 minutes and all noodles.
Mix well and serve.

title: rice casserole
directions: In a quart baking dish, combine butter, oil, green onion, green pepper, soup, water, mushrooms and rice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until rice is done.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Use butter or margarine to grease lightly an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Thoroughly mix the cocoa, sugar and salt in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk and mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Let the mixture boil, stirring occasionally, until it reaches a temperature of 234° or until a small amount of the mixture can be formed in a soft ball after being dropped in a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110° (pan barely warm to touch).
Beat with wooden spoon until fudge begins to thicken and lose gloss.
Stir in pecans and quickly spread in the prepared pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: pig feet soup
directions: Combine water, vinegar, pig's feet, salt, pepper in large stockpot.
Cover, bring to boil, and simmer until meat is tender. Stir in tomatoes, lima beans, and corn.
Bring to boil.
Remove pig's feet and debone if desired.
Reduce heat cover and simmer for about 30 minutes or until you're satisfied with taste.

title: frost delights
directions: Fold brown sugar into beaten egg white.
Spread onto cookie batter; sprinkle with chopped nuts and bake in a moderate 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 or 36.

title: squash bake
directions: Saute onion.
Add squash.
Cook until tender.
Add cheese while mixture is hot.
Moisten bread in milk and add with eggs. Beat well.
Pour into greased flat baking dish and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Add more cheese on top, if desired.

title: southern sausage biscuits
directions: Grate cheese.
Let cheese and sausage stand at room temperature.
Combine cheese, sausage and prepared biscuit mix; blend thoroughly.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 30 biscuits.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in ungreased 9-inch pan.
In bowl, mix flour and following 3 ingredients.
Stir well and pour over peaches.
Next, stir water and sugar until well dissolved and pour over peaches and batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday coffee cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set oven temperature according to package directions.
After 15 minutes in oven, remove and spread on nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Return to oven and continue baking until done, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mississippi river mud cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spoon batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until top is barely soft to touch. Remove cake from oven and cover top with marshmallows.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until marshmallows are soft.
Spread marshmallows over cake and immediately cover with chocolate frosting.
Cool thoroughly before cutting cake into squares. Makes 12 average size or 24 small servings.

title: alex's awesome soup
directions: Open cans of tomato soup; pour into a big pan.
Stir in the 2 cups of water; begin cooking this on the stove.
Stir in macaroni, spices and pepperoni.
Cook altogether until very warm.
Pour into an eating bowl and add cheese strips on top.
Yum!
Yum!

title: pickles and peanuts spread
directions: Whip together.
Put in containers and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
Can be made 3 days ahead.
Crazy, but good!

title: hot cross buns
directions: Sift together flour, salt, spices and 2 ounces sugar into a warm mixing bowl.
Rub in the butter.
Stir the remaining sugar into the warm milk and water mixture, then sprinkle the yeast over the top.
Let sit in a warm place until frothy, then add to the flour mixture.
Mix to a dough and knead on a floured board for 10 minutes.
Cover and leave to rise in a warm place for 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Combine first ten ingredients.
Add oil.
Mix all together. Add hot water.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
For soft cookies, use only 1/4 cup water and 1/2 cup flour.

title: glazed carrots and grapes
directions: Scrape carrots and cut into 1-inch slices.
Boil in water with salt and white sugar about 25 minutes until tender.
Drain off liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan with brown sugar and orange juice.
Add Grand Marnier with mixture bubbles.
Add carrots and grapes.
Do not overcook.

title: quickie rolls
directions: Mix well.
Grease muffin pan; fill half full.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts and serve with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
