directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir undiluted soup, eggs, mayonnaise and onion until well blended.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
If using fresh mushrooms, add now.
Remove from heat and add rice, French onion soup and beef soup.
If using canned mushrooms, add at this time. Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pineapple bavarian(sugar-free)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in 1/2 cup cold water and the pineapple with its juice.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
In a large bowl, prepare topping mix as label directs using skim milk.
Fold thickened gelatin mixture into topping.
Pour into 1-quart mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour; cook over low heat, stirring, until dark brown.
Add liquid, okra, tomatoes, onion, pepper sauce, thyme and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add seafood; cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot rice.

title: cranberry-glazed cornish game hens
directions: Truss hens, sprinkle inside and out with salt and pepper. Roast according to directions on package.
Thirty minutes before hens are done, heat cranberry sauce and remaining ingredients. Brush hens with sauce every 5 minutes until hens are done.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard and set aside.
Combine meat, eggs, onion and bread crumbs and seasonings. Add 1 cup of tomato sauce and pack into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour 1/4 cup sauce over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with meat loaf.
Garnish with green pepper slices.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up sides.
Seal perforations. Bake 14 to 19 minutes.
Cool completely.
Blend sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper until smooth.
Spread over crust. Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Mix can of Eagle Brand milk and coconut together.
Spread over cake while hot. Then add drained pineapple.
Next, spread Cool Whip, then coconut.

title: pound cake - tube pan
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, mix in flour, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (about).

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into quarter sized balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Freeze.
Put in plastic bag.
Bake from frozen state at 350° for 15 minutes. Should be firm, not hard.

title: orange and raisin bars
directions: Put orange and raisins through food chopper.
Put soda in sour milk.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: grilled greek lamb chops
directions: Prick the lamb chops with sharp fork, then place in shallow bowl.
In a small bowl, combine lemon juice, mint, paprika, cinnamon, nutmeg and garlic.
Pour over chops, turning once so entire surface is covered with the marinade.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Drain chops.
Grill or broil 5 minutes on each side. Serve over rice.
Low-fat and tasty.

title: icing
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and add cooled milk mix. Beat until creamy and smooth and doubled.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet. Drain.
Mix Rice Krispies, Cheddar cheese, celery soup and eggs together in a large bowl. Add sausage and onion to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Trim fat and bone from pork.
Cut onion into thin slices.
Mix mustard, soup and water in a bowl.
Coat bottom of casserole dish with thin layer of soup mixture.
Arrange pork chops in casserole dish, lay sliced onions on top.
Cover with remainder of soup mixture.
Bake, covered, in oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: *May substitute pieces of choice.
Pork chops work well in this recipe, also.

title: crab meat bisque
directions: Place all ingredients into blender and mix.
Pour into saucepan and heat thoroughly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, cook and pull meat off bone.
Melt butter. Saute onion, celery, pepper and mushrooms until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Boil 1/2 package spaghetti (in chicken broth if you want to).
Mix chicken, cream of mushroom soup and spaghetti well.
Pour into baking dish and grate cheese over top. Bake at 400° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: calabasitas zucchini casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet; place zucchini in pan and stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Stir in onion and garlic; stir-fry 5 more minutes.

title: italian beef on a bun
directions: Cook roast(s) in crock-pot or slow cooker because broth is needed.
Lift out meat and shred up.
To the broth, add the remaining spices.
Add meat to broth and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Spoon onto buns when ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Combine rice and onion soup; place over bottom of casserole.
Place chicken on top of mixture. Pour 2 cans of water and can of soup over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cheese spread
directions: Ingredients should be at room temperature.
Whip slowly with mixer until fluffy.
Spread on French bread.
Broil until done.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; heat until shortening melts.
Cool.
Place yeast in a large bowl.
Add milk mixture; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in 3 cups flour.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining 2 cups flour, baking powder, soda and salt, stirring well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 8 hours or up to 5 days.
Punch down dough.
Shape into 36 balls (1 1/2-inch).
Place dough balls 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old english eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks in mixer bowl until thick.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light.
Add cream; beat well.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add confectioners sugar gradually, beating well after each addition. Beat until soft peaks form.
Fold gently into chilled mixture. Chill, covered, for 1 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread. Add bacon, pepper, onion and Miracle Whip. Then add salt and tomatoes. Mix gently.

title: ray's ultimate ham roll-ups
directions: Allow cream cheese to reach room temperature and thoroughly blend with bacon-horseradish dip. Spread mixture heavily onto slice of shaved ham and roll each one into a log. Cut each log into 3 pieces and insert a toothpick into each one. Arrange Ham Roll-Ups in a spoke pattern, place on a large serving platter.

title: cornish hens steamed in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season each hen with salt, pepper, sage and parsley.
Wrap each hen in foil.
Place hens on baking sheet or in baking pan.
Cook in oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove hens from oven and raise heat to 425°.
Open foil to expose hens.
(Be careful of steam.)
Brush each hen with 2 teaspoons margarine. Return uncovered hens to oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until browned.

title: baked cabbage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in 9 x 13 baking dish. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package or steam fresh.
Poach chicken until tender and juices run clear.
Slice chicken breasts in 1/2 to make thinner.
Cover bottom of glass casserole with broccoli and layer chicken on top.
Mix everything else and pour on.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Broil top until brown.
Best served with wild rice.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat sugar and oleo until fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs - mix well.
Add alternately:
2 cups all-purpose flour and l cup sour cream.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 35-40 mins.

title: fish in garlic sauce(garlicky, but good!)
directions: Arrange fillets side by side in greased baking dish.
Mix 3 cloves garlic with 3 tablespoons olive oil and spread over fillets.
Squeeze juice of 1 orange over all and sprinkle with pepper.
Bake in hot oven, 450°, for about 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Fry the rest of garlic in remaining olive oil.
Remove the garlic and fry parsley 3 minutes.
Add juice of the other orange, salt and a little pepper.
Pour over fish before serving.
Serves 6.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and pepper (optional) and toss with sugar. Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Hold boil for 3 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Pour cooled mixture over cabbage mixture and refrigerate for up to 2 weeks or package in freezer containers and freeze for use later.
Great for unexpected guests or for plan ahead dinners.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add tomato sauce, drained corn, salsa, refried beans and taco seasoning mix. Simmer, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. In a separate bowl, combine cottage cheese, eggs and oregano.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with 5 tortillas, overlapping edges.
Top with half of the meat mixture. Spoon 1/2 of the cottage cheese mixture over meat.
Repeat layers of tortillas, meat and cottage cheese. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and casserole bubbles.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, combine hamburger, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and steak sauce.
Layer in the following order:
sauce, noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water; add all other ingredients. Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: hamburger bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet and drain well.
Add salt and pepper to taste, onions, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Let simmer.
Mash both cans of beans in blender until smooth and add to mixture.
Pour into Pyrex dish and top with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or bake in microwave for about 5 minutes.

title: salmon rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss gently.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Boil water in a saucepan large enough to hold the number of eggs you want to boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Take eggs from refrigerator and with a needle or pin, make a small hole through the shell in the center of the fat end of the egg.
Turn heat to slow boil and stir from time to time.
As soon as eggs are put in water, start timing, 5 to 6 minutes for soft boiled, 11 minutes for hard boiled.
With both soft and hard boiled eggs, fill another saucepan with cold water and ice if possible.
As soon as eggs are finished cooking, remove from hot water and instantly put them in the cold water.
Soft eggs can stay in the cold water about 15 to 30 seconds and then be served while the hard boiled eggs can stay in the cold water up to five minutes before peeling.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream margarine in a large bowl or mixer.
Gradually beat in cheese and other ingredients except flour.
Beat thoroughly, then gradually blend in flour.
Shape in 4 rolls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate several hours or days.

title: spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble into small pieces.
In a jar, combine bacon with 2 tablespoons bacon fat, lemon juice, salad oil, sugar, tarragon and salt and shake until well combined. Thoroughly wash spinach and break into bite size pieces.
Add onion, celery and orange sections.
Pour dressing over all and toss until well coated.
If desired, use half as much spinach and use lettuce and tomatoes.

title: italian fried zucchini
directions: In small bowl, lightly whisk egg, gradually sift in flour and salt, whisk until smooth.
Slowly whisk in 1/3 cup water, batter will be like pancake batter.
Let set 15-20 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix the flour, salt and cream of tartar.
In a small saucepan, add the water, slowly stirring constantly to prevent lumps.
Add the cooking oil.
Add food color until you get desired color. Cook over medium heat; stir until mixture becomes very thick. Remove from heat; allow to cool.
Knead.
Store in covered container.

title: preacher cookies
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: senorita betty's fiesta taco dip
directions: Mix and place on flat plate; top with grated Cheddar cheese, chopped tomatoes, green peppers and/or green onions.
Serve with nachos for dipping.

title: bread pudding
directions: Remove
crust from bread.
(I use the crust.) Butter and dice it
and
soak
in
milk.
Add other ingredients and blend well. (I
add coconut and raisins to taste.) Pour into greased baking dish.
Place
baking
dish
in pan of hot water in 325° oven for 30 minutes or until top of pudding is firm, crusty and lightly browned.
Yield:
2 servings.
Bread pudding should be removed from oven and allow to cool for 10 or 15 minutes before serving. Recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and meal together.
Mix in eggs.
Stir in syrup, butter and vanilla.
Add pecans.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix milk with 2 cups self-rising flour.
Add more flour to stiffen dough.
Place dough on a floured board and roll out to a thickness of about 1/2 inch.
Cut into 3 or 4-inch rectangles.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Put boiling water in bowl.
Add Jello and mix well.
Let gel slightly and add crushed pineapple, juice and all and the sour cream.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: brisket supreme
directions: Place brisket in Dutch oven.
Combine beer, chili sauce, brown sugar and catsup in mixing bowl.
Mix well and pour over brisket. Bake at 275° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Cool meat and slice.
Reheat when ready to serve.
Can be prepared days ahead of time since meat slices much easier when chilled.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bring chicken and water to boiling in a large kettle; skim off foam.
Add onion, 1 carrot, celery, salt, dill and cloves.
Cover kettle, lower heat and cook 1 hour, or until chicken is tender.

title: no-cholesterol cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, margarine and baking soda; beat with an electric mixer until well combined.
Add butter flavoring and vinegar; combine thoroughly.
While mixer is running, add flour, a little at a time, stopping mixer often to scrape down sides of bowl.
Mix until dough is creamy.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Dissolve cinnamon candy in the boiling water.
Add Jell-O and stir until all is dissolved.
Add applesauce and crushed pineapple.
Put in mold and refrigerate until firmly set.
This is delicious with all meat dishes.

title: spaghetti spinach casserole
directions: Lightly oil 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and onion. Stirring frequently, cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in spinach; cook 2 minutes longer.
Stir in cottage cheese, salt, nutmeg and pepper until smooth.
Toss with spaghetti until well coated.
Place in prepared baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella. Bake in 425° oven 20 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted and slightly brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix with hands.
Roll into ball or roll.

title: banana bread cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour loaf pan.
Mix butter and honey in large bowl with beaters until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, bananas, milk and Tia Maria.
Sift together salt, baking powder, baking soda and flour.
Gradually mix all ingredients into banana batter.
Spoon into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool before removing.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Line pan with Twinkies, cream side up.
Mix pudding with milk. Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Beat with mixer.
Pour mixture over Twinkies.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef or pork and drain.
Cook sausage and add to the ground beef.
Mix together cottage cheese, 2 eggs and salt.
Set aside.
Cook lasagna noodles until tender and drain on wax paper or Reynolds wrap.
Layer in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers two or three times.
Top with remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Cook in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Wait 10 or 15 minutes and serve.

title: divinity candy
directions: Beat egg whites in large bowl and set aside.
Combine next 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil quickly (don't scorch). Continue to boil until syrup forms hard ball when dropped in cool water (cracks against side).
Turn large mixer bowl with egg whites on medium and pour hot syrup over them steadily with stream about size of spaghetti until all syrup is used up.
Continue beating and scrape candy down from side of bowl.
Beat until candy starts to firm up and lose its shiny appearance.
While beating, add vanilla, then nuts and spoon out on buttered dish with teaspoon.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; set aside to cool.
Mix flour and sugar together. Add milk and eggs; beat well.
Stir in vinegar and vanilla.
Add melted butter and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Yield: 9-inch pie.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add dates, granulated sugar and eggs. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Stir in Rice Krispies and nuts, mixing well.
Shape into balls and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Can be made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to bake and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dad's special soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
In a large kettle mix soup and water.
Add hamburg and Italian seasoning.
Simmer until hot.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add apples, eggs, salad oil and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 50 minutes.
(Can be baked in two smaller pans. Makes a good sized cake.)

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Add baking soda, salt and red pepper.
Sift two more times.
Grate cheese and butter.
When soft enough, add flour a little at a time and mix all ingredients well. (I put cheese and butter in microwave on defrost for just a few seconds to help soften.)
You can use a pastry utensil or work it with your hands to mix.
Put through cookie press and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brownness desired.
Makes approximately 90 to 100 straws about 3 to 3 1/2 inches long.
(I used cookie press disc with a star-like shape.)

title: heavenly salad(heritage recipe)
directions: Stir in Jello while dry.
Mix together and chill.
Makes a really good dish.

title: the best friend a steak ever had
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Halve buttons if large.
Melt butter in small skillet.
Saute buttons 2 to 3 minutes.
Add slices and continue to saute until all are browned.
Reduce heat.
Add dry seasonings to taste.
Stir and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soy and Worcestershire.
Increase heat slightly.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes. Add sherry.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until sherry cooks down.
Keep warm until steaks are done.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place ribs in a kettle and add cold water to cover.
Bring to a boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Drain and run cold water over meat. Return bones to a clean kettle and add 3 quarts of water and salt to taste.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes, skimming surface to remove scum.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Place sugar, cream of tartar, vanilla and egg white in small mixer bowl; mix well.
Add boiling water to egg mixture.
Beat with a beater on high speed until mix will stand in stiff peaks. Makes 3 cups.
Ices 2 (8-inch) layer cakes.

title: microwavable tender buttery corn
directions: Mix corn, margarine, salt, pepper and nutmeg in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 3 minutes; stir. Cover and microwave 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken pie casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into casserole dish.

title: irish stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat.
Save remaining flour.
Brown meat in hot fat in a 4 quart saucepan.
Add water and cover.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions, potatoes, turnip and carrots.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes. Add peas.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Blend water with remaining flour.
Add to stew.
Stir; cook until thick. Serves 6.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix together. Chill at least 6 hours. Make into 1/2-inch balls. Bake 25 to 30 minutes on cookie sheet at 350°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: pig-pickin cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pickled beans
directions: Wash, string and break beans. Boil beans in a large pot until almost tender or until a bean will mash between fingers. Cool quickly in ice water. Pack in quart jars. Add 2 teaspoons pickling or canning salt to each quart. Also add 1 teaspoon vinegar to each jar. Fill with cold water and put 2 piece lids on each jar. Set in a cool dark place. There is no need to seal jars. Set jars in a box or on papers because water will ooze out of jars during fermentation. Do not open for about 3 or 4 weeks.

title: taco squares or wedges
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef, drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Stir to blend and set aside.
In a separate bowl blend sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion; set aside.
Mix Bisquick and water until a soft dough forms.
Press into bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of greased 8-inch square or round baking dish.
Spread beef mixture over dough; sprinkle with peppers and sliced tomatoes.
Spread sour cream and cheese mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl; mix wet ingredients together and add to dry mixture.
Pour into greased muffin tins; bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: flowerpot cake
directions: You will need 1 clear plastic flowerpot, artificial flower and a 3 x 5-inch index card.

title: bar-be-cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In large skillet brown beef, then drain. Next add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onion to beef. Mix well. Place each biscuit into cupcake section of cupcake pan and press out to line cup up sides.
Do not grease pan.
Now spoon meat mixture to fill each cup evenly.
Fill any empty cups 1/2 full with water to prevent warping.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400° until tops of biscuits are golden.
Remove.
Turn off oven. Sprinkle shredded cheese evenly over tops.
Return to oven a few minutes to melt cheese.
Serves 2 adults.

title: special k squares
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and margarine to boil.
Boil one minute or a little less.
Immediately add peanut butter and the Special K cereal.
Mix as quickly as possible.
Put into large cake pan. Melt chocolate chips and spread thinly over cereal mixture.
Cut into squares when cool.
Work quickly as mixture sets up fast.

title: barbecued sauce for chicken
directions: Bring to boil and pour over fried chicken. Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350° (covered).

title: seven layer bars
directions: In an oblong pan, put the ingredients into pan as listed (layer).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, nutmeg and salt; beat well.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour in pie shell and bake until set.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix crumbs with margarine.
Save 1/2 for topping.
Put remaining crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream.
Spread on crumbs.
Refrigerate until hard. Spread with whipped topping.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Top with Butterfingers.
Chill and enjoy.
Serves 12.

title: cold tarragon chicken breasts
directions: Brush tarragon and melted butter on the breasts.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add wine. Bake 15 minutes more. Refrigerate before serving.
Excellent alternative picnic or luncheon dish.

title: mom's chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain in large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 2 hours.

title: picante sauce
directions: Drop tomatoes in boiling water for 30 seconds.
Remove and place in cold water, then peel, core and quarter.
Place small amounts of tomatoes, onions, peppers and carrots in container of processor. Blend until finely chopped.
Repeat until all vegetables are chopped.
Combine vegetables and remaining ingredients in a large pot.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes. Pour into hot jars.
Adjust lids and process 15 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yields about 12 quarts.

title: mystery salad
directions: Mix gelatin according to directions and let set until thickened a little.
Mix mayonnaise, cream and cream cheese.
Add to gelatin with pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Pour into mold or serving dish.
Chill.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix with Eagle Brand milk.
Shape in loaf pan and refrigerate.

title: very good sweet potato pie
directions: Beat potatoes with mixer until free of lumps.

Add remainder of ingredients and beat well. Pour into one 9-inch unbaked crust and bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then lower baking temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain; add margarine or meat drippings to season.
(I prefer meat drippings.)
Add tomatoes to macaroni.
Cook on low heat just until tomatoes are thoroughly heated.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Scald milk.
Add the sugar and salt to the milk and stir until both are thoroughly dissolved.
Add eggs; use blender.
Add the cream and stir in vanilla; cool.
Turn into freezer.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugars and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and milk; blend well.
Gradually add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 10 minutes at 375°.
Press a Kiss in center of ball to flatten as soon as you remove from oven.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Bake cookies according to package directions.
Let cool. Press 1 tablespoon of ice cream between 2 cookies.
Place in jelly roll pan and freeze until firm.
Melt chips and butter in double boiler, stirring occasionally.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Dip half of each sandwich into chocolate.
Place in pan and freeze until firm.
Store in plastic wrap.

title: jackie's macaroni & cheese
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse in cold water and set aside to drain. In saucepan, melt butter; add flour, salt & pepper.
Cook until golden.
Add milk and simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add Parmesan and macaroni; pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15-20 minutes.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon olive oil until transparent. Add chicken, chilies, broth and beans. Add spices and heat 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue sauce for pork chops
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Place 6 or 8 pork chops in a baking dish and cover with the sauce. Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 325° oven.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and 1/2 cup milk; cook to soft ball stage.
Take off burner and add vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Beat by hand until smooth and pour into buttered glass candy dish.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large 14 x 10-inch casserole and bake for 2 hours at 325°, covered.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour if you want a browned top. Do not add salt as olive juice and Fritos have enough. Serve hot.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and freeze.
When ready to serve, put in punch bowl and add the 7-Up.
This recipe makes 75 servings.

title: "failure proof" cream sauce
directions: Put the butter, flour and salt into a medium-sized saucepan. Turn the heat to "low."
Put the saucepan on the stove.

Stir the butter and flour mixture over low heat until the butter and flour are smooth and well mixed (that will take about 2 minutes). Gradually pour the large can of Carnation evaporated milk into the saucepan.
Stir your cream sauce with a wooden spoon until the sauce is smooth and creamy.
It will take 3 to 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: seafood over angel hair pasta
directions: In 12 inch skillet, heat Italian dressing and cook shallots over medium high heat 2 minutes. Add carrots and snow peas and cook 2 minutes. Add broth. Bring to a boil; add shrimp, scallops and mussels. Simmer covered 3 minutes or until seafood is done and mussel shells open. (Discard any unopened shells.) Stir in cream blended with flour and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened. Stir in salt and pepper. Serve over
hot pasta and sprinkle, if desired, with freshly ground pepper and grated parmesan cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: uncle elmer's stew
directions: Brown meat, add cabbage, onion and peppers.
Pour tomatoes over top, cover and simmer.
Can be put in crock-pot as well.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of cookie sheet with rolls.
Lay out flat and press down perforations.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, mayo, sour cream and dressing mix until smooth.
Spread on cool crust.
Chop vegetables very fine; toss with cheese and sprinkle over creamy layer.
Sprinkle with bacon and place onion rings on top.
Cut and serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets until done.
Peel and mash. Add butter, sugar and vanilla.
Combine the beaten eggs and milk. Mix with potatoes until well blended.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press hamburger in bottom of dish.
Pour cream of chicken over meat (do not dilute).
Place Tater Tots over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.

title: baked vidalia onion
directions: Peel and core onion.
Stuff center with butter.
Pour brown sugar over the top.
Place in microwave-safe dish sized to hold the onions.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes per onion.

title: creole kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa into small slices.
Place in pan and brown.
Drain off fat.
Add shrimp and continue to brown for 5 minutes.
Add okra and corn.
Cook for 5 more minutes.
Then add tomato sauce and diced tomatoes, seasonings and bell pepper.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes on low.
Serve over rice.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil. Cool. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip; stir until well blended. Put into your favorite mold and freeze. Remove from freezer about 10 minutes before serving. Loosen around edges with knife and slice in desired portions.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix until creamy.
Spoon into reserved egg white halves. Sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Butter a shallow casserole dish.
Combine cream cheese, soup, milk, salt and pepper in a blender; blend well.
Grate carrots and add to cream cheese mixture.
Mix well and pour into a casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs, melted butter and cheese and sprinkle over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put 4 teaspoons of mix in cup and add boiling water.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls in pan to make a pizza crust.
Cook sausage and drain.
Crumble sausage on crust.
Add hash browns.
Add eggs to milk and pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook at 375° until eggs are set and crust is lightly browned.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix well and place in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Put a tube of Ritz (or similar) crackers, crushed, over the top.
Pour 1 stick melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions and boned chicken in oleo.
Mix into this the soup.
Heat until bubbling.
Layer broken tortillas, soup and chicken mixture and cheese alternately into baking dish (glass is best).
Repeat the layering until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix until soft ball, press into a 9 x 13 inch greased and floured pan (do not use glass).
Be sure the crust is pressed very high on the sides of the pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: top ramen salad
directions: Prepare vegetables: shred cabbage, slice onions (including stems), grate carrots, use uncooked frozen peas, dice celery and drain water chestnuts.
Toss together.
Add chopped, cooked chicken (2 cans prepared).
Break up Ramen (uncooked) in small pieces, using handle of knife before opening package.

title: german chocolate cookies
directions: Cut one bar of chocolate into bits and set aside.
Melt the other over boiling water or very low heat.
Cool.
Mix sugars, butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add melted chocolate.
Then gradually add the flour to which the salt and baking powder have been added.
Gradually mix in the chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage and remove from grease.
Set aside.
Fry hen to golden brown and remove from oil.
Cool and debone.
Pour off most of oil where chicken was fried.
Add onions to oil and saute.
Then add celery, pepper and garlic with a little water.
Add chicken and sausage to vegetables.
Reduce heat.
Cover and let simmer until chicken is tender.
Add water and let come to a rapid boil.
Add uncooked rice.
Stir slowly.
Let come to a boil and then reduce heat as low as possible.
Occasionally lift rice from bottom of pot without stirring.
Let cook on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery in butter.
In 2-quart casserole, mix sauteed vegetables with rice and broccoli.
Mix chicken soup and milk, then pour over rice mixture.
Spread Cheez Whiz over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: lemon lightning cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar and dry gelatin.
Combine in a small mixing bowl the eggs, milk and oil; stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Beat vigorously by hand 1 minute until smooth.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: big game corned meat(wild game; can also use other meat)
directions: Stir all ingredients thoroughly (except meat).
Add boned meat.
Cover with plate and put a heavy weight on it.
Leave meat in brine for 48 hours or more.
Remove from brine, wash and tie to keep in shape.
Place it in cold water to cover.
Bring it to the boiling point.
Remove the scum, cover it and simmer for 4 to 5 hours.
Skim at intervals.
Let it cool in broth.
Serve it with any horseradish sauce.
You can also follow any cookbook recipe such as corned beef and cabbage, etc.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix and sprinkle one box of any flavor jello over all and stir.

title: holiday brown bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the raisins, sugar and butter or margarine.
Pour the boiling water over the mixture. Cover and set aside for 8 to 10 hours or overnight.

title: glen's punch
directions: Mix sugar and water
to dissolve sugar.
Add all juices and mix well.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Mix onions, 3 1/2 cups cheese and remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Place venison and onion in slow cooker.
Combine the next 7 ingredients; pour over venison.
Cover and cook on high for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
In small bowl, combine cornstarch, sour cream and horseradish; mix well.
Gradually stir into venison mixture.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer or until sauce is thickened.
Serve over noodles.

title: cranberry-orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-cup Bundt or 10-inch tube pan. For cake, beat sugar and margarine until creamy.
Stir in milk, eggs and 2 teaspoons grated orange peel.
Gradually add combined flour, oats, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Fold in cranberries.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Layer avocado dip, mushrooms, onions, tomatoes, bacon, Cheddar cheese and olives.
Use Tostitos for dipping.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, paprika and pepper.
Brown rice and onion in butter.
Spread rice mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered baking dish. Add broth and celery salt.
Place chicken on top of rice-broth mixture.
Cover dish tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer or until meat is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cube potatoes; boil 15 minutes.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix flour with milk; add to potatoes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add small cube Velveeta cheese; simmer.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat in a large heavy pot until it loses its color. Drain off fat.
Add onion, peppers (or chiles), garlic and mushrooms.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, and mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Sprinkle cheese on each serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: mushroom soup(low-fat)
directions: Coat a large Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add margarine and place over medium heat until margarine melts.
Add green onions and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and saute 3 minutes. Sprinkle flour over vegetables; stir and cook 1 minute.
Gradually add broth and next 4 ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease cast-iron skillet and place in oven to heat.
Mix ingredients, reserving sausage.
Mix well.
Add sausage.
Mix.
Pour batter into hot skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, peeling the skins off and slice while still warm.
Heap chopped onions in center of potatoes.
Top with sugar, salt and pepper.
Fry cut up bacon, stirring, until crisp.
Skim bacon from frying pan; set aside.
Add water and vinegar to bacon grease and bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes and onions and toss this mixture lightly to mix well.
Add bacon, crumbled, last.
Slice boiled eggs to garnish top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy freezer jam
directions: Stir strawberries and sugar, mixing thoroughly.
Set aside. Stir Sure-Jell fruit pectin and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir mixture together until sugar is completely dissolved and no longer grainy.
Pour into containers.
Cover.
Let stand overnight.
Store in freezer until ready to use.
After opening, store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 (8 ounce) containers.

title: mexican salad
directions: Cut up lettuce, cheese, onion and tomatoes.
At last minute before serving add beans and 1 (8-ounce) bottle of Catalina salad dressing.
Then add crushed Fritos.

title: texas brownies
directions: Combine margarine, coffee and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour this hot mixture over flour and sugar. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Bake in long pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
While brownies are cooking, prepare icing.
Ice as soon as you take them out of the oven.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Put orange jello in bowl (dry). Then add other ingredients.
Mix well and chill overnight.

title: savory sauerkraut casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and molasses. Add dry ingredients. Refrigerate.
Roll into balls and dip in sugar.
Press down with a glass. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar. Add egg.
Add buttermilk and oil, beating until mixture is smooth.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked.
Serve with maple syrup.
Yields 8 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix and serve.
Really nice at Christmas or St. Patrick's Day.

title: rice krispies-caramel bars
directions: Melt 1 1/2 bags miniature
marshmallows and 1/2 cup margarine.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix together.
Grease two cookie sheets.
Spread 1/2 mixture on each pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 package marshmallows onto one pan.
Melt caramels until almost melted and add condensed milk and 1/3 cup margarine.
Heat until melted.
When melted, pour over the pan with the marshmallows.
Take the other pan of Rice Krispies mixture and put on top of caramel and marshmallow mixture.

title: tomato cheeseburgers(variation of sloppy joes)
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion; drain meat.
Add small can tomatoes.
Cook (simmer) until juice is cooked down (15 minutes). Add 6 ounces chopped Cheddar cheese.
Simmer 1 minute.
Serve on buns.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream together oleo or margarine and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt. Add alternately the dry ingredients and water. Add sauerkraut. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched. Bake in two 8-inch pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan. Frost with your favorite icing.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add pineapple. Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter on low heat; cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Shape into 2 rolls, 2-inches in diameter. Roll each in coconut and refrigerate.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices. Yields 2 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, deviled ham, sauce, mustard, salt and onions.
Mix well into a ball and roll in pecan pieces. Chill.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and butter; form into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet and chill.
Melt chocolate bar and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip each peanut butter ball into chocolate. Keep chocolate at low temperature while dipping. These freeze beautifully and taste great right out of the freezer.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour out onto floured paper and knead into a long roll; pinch off biscuits and put on greased pan. Cook at 350° until brown on bottom, 15 to 25 minutes.
Brown on top slightly under the broiler.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon of the butter and remove from pan.
Melt remaining butter in same pan; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Stir in milk and cook until sauce thickens and boils.
Stir in cooked chicken strips, cooked spaghetti pieces and mushrooms.
Spoon in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until crumbs are toasted.
Serves 4 generously.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Scald milk, but do not boil.
Add butter and molasses to the milk and let it cool.
Mix yeast and lukewarm water.
Add sugar and salt to yeast mixture.
Add the yeast mixture to cool milk. Add 2 cups of rye flour and 6 to 8 cups of sifted white flour. Knead on floured board.
Let the dough rise in a greased bowl until doubled in size.
After it has risen, punch it down and make the dough into 3 loaves.
Let the dough rise again in 3 bread pans or 1 pound coffee cans that have been floured and greased.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
May be frozen.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Add 1 c. nuts. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make pudding according to package directions. Add cream cheese and Cool Whip. Mix together well. Crush cookies to look like dirt. Put layer of cookies in bottom of a 13 x 9 pan. Put layer of pudding mix. Put layer of cookies on top. Decorate with gummy worms.

title: heavenly broiled bass
directions: Place fillets in single layer on well-oiled baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients and spread mixture on fish.
Broil fish 6 inches from source of heat approximately 10 minutes or until top is lightly browned and fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Serves 6.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Mix honey and dressing for marinade.
Place chicken breasts, cut in strips, in 1/2 marinade in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Pour out marinade.
Grill chicken until done, basting with remaining marinade that chicken was not in.

title: beef stroganoff(easy, but delicious!)
directions: Flour and brown steak in as little shortening as possible. Completely cover with water; add soup mix and cook slowly, covered about 2 hours or until tender.
Add mushrooms when meat is almost done. Stir in sour cream and just barely simmer for 10 minutes. Serve over buttered noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian casserole
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook ground meat and onion until onion is tender, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add next 7 ingredients; cook 2 minutes to blend flavors.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, evenly spoon 1/3 meat mixture.
Arrange potatoes on top.
Repeat with meat mixture.
Cover dish tightly with foil. Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Remove foil; sprinkle mixture evenly with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes for easier cutting.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut up and cook broccoli and rice.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz, rice, milk and butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix flour, pecans and butter and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly golden.
Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Spread over cooled bottom layer.
Mix puddings and milk together.
Beat well.
Place this on top of the second layer. Then spread remaining Cool Whip over top of mixture.

title: smothered pork steak
directions: Place pork steaks in a baking pan. Bake in oven at 400° for 40 mins. then turn and bake additional 15 minutes. Pour off drippings and save to add to soups. Mix mushroom soup with onion soup mix,
then add about 3 to 4 tbsp. of drippings drained from meat. Pour over steaks and bake until soups are bubbly.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first nine ingredients, blending dry ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Divide the batter between two 9-inch layer cake pans sprayed with nonstick cooking spray or use a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake for about 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cakes on rack, then remove from pans.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix and boil the sugar, water, butter, beaten egg, flour and vinegar until thickens, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients, except banana.
Add the cut up banana just before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: turkey or chicken loaf
directions: Cook turkey or chicken into small pieces; add bread crumbs and celery.
Beat egg yolks, wine and cream into egg yolks.
Add salt and onions.
Mix all together.
Pack into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with gravy or mushroom sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: You may have to mix the ingredients with your hands.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.
One cup each of nuts and dates may be added.
Makes a dishpan full.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cut center from
cabbage, chop it and set aside.
Plunk the head of cabbage into
a
large pot with a cup of water and steam a couple of minutes.	Separate the leaves.
Mix together hamburger, browned
slightly, sausage, salt, spices, rice, egg and onion. Plunk
large spoonfuls into each leaf and roll up. Put the chopped cabbage
heart
in bottom of a large pot.
Top with cabbage rolls, seam side down.
Pour V-8 juice and water over the top, bring
to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and barely simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bread pudding and brandy sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine bread, milk and cream.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar.
Add bread mixture.
Stir in vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon, butter and raisins.
Pour into a buttered, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Set in a larger shallow pan.
Pour hot water into larger pan (depth of 1 inch).
Bake 1 hour, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm, with Brandy Sauce.

title: chicken and rice casserole #2
directions: Heat soup and milk until just boiling.
Stir in chicken, rice, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes with lid on.
Sprinkle rest of cheese and onions on top.
Bake additional 5 minutes with lid off.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta, then cool.
Combine all ingredients and mix. Chill for approximately 2 hours before serving.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In large hot pot, sear meat.
When it is well seared, remove from pot.
Add cut up onions, cabbage and tomatoes to drippings left in pot and cook until they are soft.
Put meat back into mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on medium flame for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Take one stick butter and melt in cake pan.
Mix the ingredients and pour over the melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: easy made hot rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, measure sugar, shortening, salt and hot water.
Measure lukewarm water and add to it dry yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
When the sugar and shortening mixture is lukewarm, add yeast mixture.
Then add flour gradually.
Mix well.

title: veal with pepper and onions
directions: Coat large skillet with
nonstick vegetable cooking spray. Heat until hot. Add veal. Brown over medium-high heat.
Push veal to one side.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is lightly browned.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pumpkin, vanilla, peel and juice.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Add to oleo mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: cheese cake muffins
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of a muffin liner and add mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°. Can be frozen for future use.
When ready to serve, top with your favorite pie filling.
Makes approximately 18.

title: monkey bread(cinnamon sweet bread)
directions: Combine
cup
sugar
and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon. Pinch biscuits
into
bite
size pieces and roll each piece in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place biscuits in layers in a greased Bundt pan.

title: beef and cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef until brown.
Drain grease.
Stir in oregano, basil, tomato paste and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Make layers of beef mixture, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in pie plate.
Beat eggs, add milk and then add Bisquick mix, salt and pepper. Beat until well blended.
Pour over hamburg and cheese layers.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until brown.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese over top and let cool for 5 minutes.

title: italian sausage and zucchini
directions: Cook sausage until brown and onion until soft, after placing in large skillet.
Stir occasionally.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir and cook until tomatoes thicken.
Serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring water to a rolling boil and add the rice.
Cook about 20 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir.
Scald the milk in a double boiler and add the raisins.
Turn to low for 10 minutes.
Slowly stir in the cinnamon.

title: chicken cheddar casserole
directions: Mix chicken, onion, celery and green peppers with salad dressing like chicken salad.
Spread half on bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Toast bread, cut and layer alternately with salad.
Beat eggs and combine with milk.
Pour over chicken.
Let sit at least 1 hour or overnight.
Before you put it in the oven, pour 1 can of cream of mushroom soup over.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Last 10 minutes of baking, sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Cream together 1/4 pound butter, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add the eggs; beat well.
Sift together the baking powder, baking soda and flour.
Add to butter mixture; beat together.
Mix in sour cream, dates and nuts.
Lightly grease bottom and sides of tube pan.
Pour 1/2 batter into the pan.
Mix 3 teaspoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/3 of it on batter.
Add the rest of the batter in the pan.
Sprinkle rest of sugar and cinnamon mix on top.
Pour 3 tablespoons melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: green goop
directions: Please make exactly as instructed.
Do not substitute.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in three layers at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: madeline's zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, for 25 minutes.
When slightly cooled, cut into small serving pieces.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, eggs and water.
Combine with flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in oats and chips.
Drop by tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: midnight mommy russian chocolate beet cake
directions: Parboil (do not cook) beets.
Peel and grate fine.
Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil and grated beets.
Melt chocolate in double boiler and add.
Sift flour and baking soda.
Add slowly to mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: deer steak
directions: After cutting steak, put in large bowl.
Fill to covering with Coke.
Add salt, garlic and meat tenderizer and stir.
Let set overnight.
Prepare skillet for frying.
Use only enough oil to keep meat from sticking.
Remove steak from bowl.
Flour each strip "good" and put in skillet.
Brown each side, then turn fire down.
Cover and simmer until tender.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers and butter into a 2-quart casserole.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top of mixture.
Pour one stick melted margarine over crackers and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fish casserole
directions: Soak fillets in milk for 2 to 3 hours.
Dip in flour and brown in butter.
Place in baking dish.
Saute bell pepper, celery, parsley and green onions in butter until limp.
Add soup, shrimp, mushrooms, lemon juice, milk and seasonings to taste.
Pour over fillets and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Combine beef in 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add onions.
Cook over medium heat 5 to 6 minutes, stirring often, until beef is lightly brown.
Add bouillon cubes.
Quarter and core cabbage.
Cut crosswise in inch wide strips, about 8 cups.
Add to meat mixture. Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally until cabbage wilts (salt to taste).
Stir in tomatoes, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes, then mix with 1 stick melted margarine. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste; add chopped onions.
Mix together mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and sour cream; add to potato mixture and mix well.
Place in a large greased casserole.
Mix stuffing mix and 1 stick melted margarine and spread over potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Can be prepared in advance and refrigerated.

title: thick n chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Place raisins in a bowl; cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 5 minutes; drain.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine the oats, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, allspice and cloves; gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave 6 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Cook in microwave until half tender, approximately 6 minutes on High.
Cook onion and carrots in microwave until "half" tender, approximately 6 minutes on High.

Mix all vegetables, 1/2 cup croutons, cream of mushroom soup, 3/4 cup cheese and 1/2 cup water in a large bowl. Place remaining croutons on top and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake approximately 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool at least 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and onions together; salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 stick oleo, soup, cheese and sour cream.
Mix 2 cups corn flakes and 1/2 stick oleo.
Pour over top and bake.

title: heavenly ambrosia(lo-cal)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least an hour.
Serves 12.

title: fruit ice cream
directions: * Any one of these are good.

title: stuffed green peppers(and stuffed zucchini and stuffed cabbage rolls)
directions: Halve the peppers lengthwise, removing stem ends, seeds and membranes.

Immerse peppers in boiling water for 3 minutes. Sprinkle insides with salt and invert on paper towels to drain. In a skillet, cook the sausage or ground beef with the onion until the meat is brown and the onion is tender.
Drain the fat.
Stir in the undrained tomatoes, uncooked rice, worcestershire sauce, water, and salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil then reduce the heat, cover, and simmer for 15-18 minutes, or until the rice is tender. Stir in 1/4 c. cheese.
Fill the peppers with the meat mixture and place them in an 8 x 8 inch baking dish with any remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes, or until heated through. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Let stand a couple minutes before serving.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and egg yolks until thickened, then add vanilla and coconut.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs. Sift dry ingredients and add to shortening mixture. Chill. Roll into walnut sized balls and roll in mixture of 3 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: refrigerator fruit cake
directions: Put oil on hands and mix all ingredients together.
Lightly pack in an oiled tube pan.
Put in the refrigerator overnight. Take out of pan and store in the refrigerator until ready to use. Before storing, wrap tightly using moisture proof wrap.

title: lemon-chocolate frost
directions: Beat 1/2 of the lemon sherbet until smooth; gradually add chocolate milk.
Pour into glasses and top with spoonfuls of remaining lemon sherbet.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 2/3 cups.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Crumble sausage into a large bowl; add cheese add mix well. Blend biscuit mix into sausage and cheese mixture with a pastry blender.
Shape into walnut size balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: about 9 dozen.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter and sugar together.
Pat in bottom of square pan. Mix well cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat Dream Whip, milk and vanilla until stiff and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spread on top of cracker crumbs; spread blueberry filling on top.
Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: haystack cookies(christmas cookies)
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler. Chop nuts.
Mix all ingredients together. Drop teaspoons of mixture on wax paper.
Let set until cool.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Arrange steak(s) in a shallow dish.
Combine brown sugar, soy sauce, ginger, garlic and sesame oil.
Blend well.
Pour over steak(s).
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 3 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Broil or barbecue to desired doneness.
(If using flank steak, slice diagonally across the grain before serving.)

title: fancy fish roll-ups
directions: Divide small broccoli spears among fillets.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Arrange in 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°.
Place quartered biscuits in large Ziploc bag with sugar (white only) and cinnamon.
Shake few pieces at a time until coated.
Layer in buttered or sprayed Bundt pan.
Pour any remaining sugar over top; and add nuts.
Bring to a boil the brown sugar and margarine.
Pour over top of biscuits in Bundt pan.
Bake at
350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Chop, cook and drain cabbage.
Saute onion in margarine.
Stir cream cheese, soup and onions into cooked cabbage with half the bread crumbs.
Mix together and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with the other half of bread crumbs.
Pour 3 tablespoons melted margarine over top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: harvest pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together 1 cup oats, 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Mix together and pat into bottom and up the sides of a 10-inch deep dish pie pan.
Combine eggs, spices, pumpkin, evaporated milk and sugar.
Pour into crust.

title: christmas fruit delites
directions: You will also need small Christmas cupcake papers.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt 2 sticks oleo.
Add cocoa and water.
Bring to boil and pour hot mixture over dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: italian sausage pasta soup
directions: Place sausage links in a large saucepan and add water to a depth of about 1/2 inch.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes until sausage is partially cooked.
Drain. Slice sausage into 1/2-inch slices.
Return to saucepan.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, tomato sauce, basil and oregano; blend well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in pasta accents.
Cover, bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: busy day casserole
directions: In large casserole, layer salted and peppered chops, then onions, then potatoes.
Mix soups and pour over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: danny's christmas cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat butter, sugar, fructose and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in eggs until smooth.
Gradually add flour mixture and beat.
Stir in candy.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tomato, pepper and onion salad
directions: Mix 1 part vinegar and 2 parts water together to cover the vegetables.
Sprinkle a little salt and pepper to taste.
A little sugar may be added, but not necessary.
Let stand a while before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough into bottom of ungreased pizza pan. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour onto cooled crust.
Add sliced fruit of your choice.
Drizzle strawberry glaze onto fruit.
Chill for at least an hour before serving.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add broccoli and blend.
Add cheese and simmer until blended.
Add soup until blended, then add rice and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Over medium heat, saute crumbled ground beef, onion, and garlic, stirring frequently.
When meat is browned, drain off any fat.
Add sugar, salt, basil, oregano, and crushed red pepper. Mix well.
Add tomatoes (cut up), tomato paste, and puree.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally until thickened (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: meat balls 'n vegetables
directions: In a bowl combine first 7 ingredients.
Shape into twenty-four 1 1/2-inch balls.
In a large skillet, melt butter; brown meat balls on all sides.
Combine soup, cheese and sage.
Meanwhile cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain.
Arrange meat balls around sides of a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon soup mixture into center.
Place cooked vegetables over top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind first 3 ingredients in food chopper (coarse).
Cover with boiling water and let stand 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Seal in clean jars.
Add hot pepper to taste.

title: barbequed cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into 8 sections.
In aluminum foil pouch, combine all ingredients.
Seal pouch.
Place on gas grill on low heat. Cook for 1 hour with lid closed.
Cabbage should be soft.
Remove and serve.
Based on palate heat tolerance, add or lessen peppers as needed.
Dish is very spicy.

title: hash brown cheese potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 stick melted oleo and 2 cups of crushed corn flakes. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin patter cake
directions: Place slice of cake, layer with thin layer of apricot jam first, then layer of pumpkin, whipped cream, then vanilla pudding. Add second layer of pound cake.
Press top layer of cake down gently.
Run a layer of whipped cream down the middle of the top of the cake.
Sprinkle with pecans, chopped finely.

title: crunchy tuna bake
directions: Prepare Creamettes according to package directions.
Drain and toss macaroni, margarine and cheese.
Drain carrots, reserving liquid.
Combine soup, 1/3 cup reserved liquid, rosemary and pepper.
Spread tuna on lightly oiled 11 x 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with macaroni mixture, then the carrots and parsley. Pour soup over all.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and top with French fried onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: mexican pork steaks
directions: Heat oil in nonstick skillet; brown pork steaks on both sides. Combine salsa, water, lemon juice and cumin; pour mixture over chops.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 servings. Preparation Time:
15 minutes.

title: corn-chili mix
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Defrost corn.
Chop chiles.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream peanut butter and butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix until smooth, roll into balls.
Melt chocolate in a double broiler and dip balls into chocolate.
Lay on wax paper.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Keep cool since they do not have wax in the chocolate.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Cooking Time: 14 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown 3 stalks of celery and small onions.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add oatmeal, raisins and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Combine salt, baking powder, spices and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Let stand for one minute.
Remove to cooling racks.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: potato caramel cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix plain flour, cinnamon, cloves, baking powder and cocoa together, then add to the butter and sugar mix.
Add potatoes, milk and vanilla.
Mix flour, raisins and dates.
Add to mixture and mix.
Spoon in three greased cake layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread Caramel Frosting on each layer.

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Mix egg, milk and oil.
Add gradually to flour and salt, beating with rotary beater until smooth.
Dip pieces of cauliflower into batter with slotted spoon.
Drain momentarily, then fry in deep fat at 365° to 375° for 2 to 5 minutes.
This is also good for okra.

title: hungarian slaw
directions: Slice first 5 ingredients very thin and put in crock or glass jar.
Bring other 6 ingredients to a boil and pour boiling hot over vegetable mixture.
Let set overnight.
Will keep for months.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer each ingredient in order given.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: man's cookies
directions: Beat first five ingredients well.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins and/or nuts and coconut.
Bake at 375 for 10 minutes.

title: freezer corn
directions: Remove corn from ears.
Mix all ingredients and put in pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Stir every 15 minutes. Cool completely.
Bag and freeze.
Add a little sugar and salt when heating to eat.

title: old fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken, reserving broth in Dutch oven; discard vegetables.
Cool chicken and bone and cut into bite size pieces. Refrigerate broth and chicken for 8 hours.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Melt butter.
Cream in sugar; add eggs.
Add 1 cup buttermilk. Add soda to remaining 1/2 cup buttermilk and add to mixture.
Using hands, add flour and salt to dates and orange slices.
Mix together.
Add to sugar-egg mixture and mix well.
Bake 3 to 4 hours in 275° oven in tube pan.

title: chicken dinner
directions: *Vegetables should equal 1 cup.

title: "green stuff"
directions: Let Cool Whip soften.
Mix in pistachio pudding and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Mmmm good.
Oh!
Add green food coloring.

title: saucy cheesy bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package.
In skillet, brown beef and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, onion, parsley, basil, garlic powder and oregano; simmer 15 minutes.
In 3-quart oblong dish, layer 1/2 sauce, noodles and cheese.
Repeat ending with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, worcestershire sauce, and pepper; gently shape into 1 inch balls.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onions until tender.
Add mushroom soup, sour cream, salt and pepper and cook.
Serve over rice, wide noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch ball.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.
Balls may be frozen, then baked after thawing.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Stir together the cereal, 1/2 cup of the flour, the sugar, salt and yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
In a small saucepan, heat the applesauce, milk and butter until very warm (120° to 130°; the butter does not need to melt).
Gradually add to the cereal mixture and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with an electric mixer, occasionally scraping the bowl.
Add the egg and another 1/2 cup of flour.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed, scraping the bowl.
By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make a stiff, sticky dough. Cover loosely with a damp towel.
Let rise in a warm place until double in volume.
Punch down the dough and shape into a loaf. Place in a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in volume.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until done.
To prevent overbrowning, cover loosely with foil during the last few minutes of baking time. Remove the loaf from the pan and cool on a wire rack.
Yield:
16 slices.

title: pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, water, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix together and add spices and sugar.
Mix until smooth.

title: broiled marinated steaks
directions: Prepare the following marinade:
Combine the pineapple juice, soy sauce, sherry, ginger, olive oil, dry mustard, curry powder and crushed garlic.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together. Save out 1 cup and put rest in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: el dorado beef cheese casserole
directions: Place beef in cold skillet.
Brown, then drain grease.
Add onion, salt, tomato sauce and water; simmer a while.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese, chilies and olives; set aside.

title: green beans greek style
directions: Snap beans.
Place in heavy bottom pan.
Grate tomatoes over top of beans.
Place onion over tomatoes.
Salt to taste.
Add water carefully down side of pan to within 1 1/2-inches of top of beans.
Cover and bring to rapid boil.
Boil hard without stirring just until no or very little water remains and beans are tender.
Dress lightly with olive oil and toss.
Best served lukewarm or cold.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix together; bake 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: chicken divan(serves 6)
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise, milk, chicken broth and cheese.
Butter baking dish.
Layer vegetables, chicken and noodles with soup mix.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with brown butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt shortening.
Add flour and mix well.
Add milk gradually; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add corn, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly; remove from heat.
Add eggs and mix well.
Grease a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour corn mixture into dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Combine crust ingredients.
Press into 8-inch pan.
Preheat oven at 350°.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Grease sides and bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins in pan, if desired.
Tear or cut bread dough in small pieces and arrange on nuts.
Melt butter; remove from heat and add brown sugar, vanilla pudding, cinnamon and milk.
Pour this mixture on top of bread and cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert pan on tray and enjoy.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bake in 350° oven in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with butter cream or sour cream frosting.

title: chocolate and oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, milk, cocoa and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in at once the oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: silo fudge
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients for 9 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: apple butter cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, oats and apple butter.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients, then slowly add to cream mixture along with the milk.
Beat until blended.
Add nuts and raisins and chill well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Dough can be stored in fridge, and cookies can be frozen in bags or tins.

title: grandma's christmas cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugars and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, spice and soda.
Measure and set out the oats, eggs, nuts, raisins and candied fruit or chocolate chips.
In a large mixing bowl with creamed mixture, add 2 cups of flour mixture, mixing well.
Add an egg, then the remaining flour mixture; mix well.
Add an egg, then remaining oats.
Work in last egg with the nuts, raisins and candied fruit or chocolate chips. (Note:
If using candied fruit, take some of the flour and mix with the fruit to keep fruit from sticking together.)
Dough should be stiff, but moist.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes, depending on size of cookie.
Yields 8 dozen large to 16 dozen medium cookies.

title: easy pork chops and stuffing
directions: Put croutons in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle onions over croutons.
Put pork chops over onions.
Heat soup and water over medium heat until hot and smooth.
Pour over pork chops. Bake covered 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil 4 or 5 minutes. Beat until cool.

title: pina colada squares
directions: In a medium bowl, mix gelatin with sugar substitute.
Add hot pineapple juice and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved. Stir in vanilla ice milk, flaked coconut and rum extract and blend thoroughly.

title: shrimp louisiana
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft; add shrimp (fresh or canned), broken in pieces; brown.
Stir in flour, salt, chili powder and then gradually the milk.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato catsup and parsley; cover and steam for several minutes.
Serve over hot rice and/or toast.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Use 12-inch Bundt pan (greased).
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli florets into bite-sized pieces and add diced onion and Cheddar cheese.
