I always do the bacon in microwave with paper towels to absorb the grease.
Add bacon.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place in medium oven. As mixture browns, stir.

title: coffee cake
directions: Add eggs, milk, cream cheese, vanilla, flour, baking powder, soda, to creamed butter and sugar.
Mix well add blueberries last.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly and add sugar, syrup, butter and pecans. Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° until done.

title: unbelievable fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat, stirring constantly. Take off heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over sugar and cocoa that has been blended together.
Mix quickly.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press in nuts.
Let set 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: turkey ham casserole
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add next 3 ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add turkey, chestnuts and ham.

title: ripe tomato chili sauce
directions: Put tomatoes, onions, celery, peppers and apples in large pot. Add remaining ingredients; boil and simmer until thick.
(You need to watch it when it starts to get thick, as it burns easily; stir often.)
Store in clean, glass jars.

title: hot water cocoa cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Combine the shortening, sugar, eggs and 1 cup hot water.
Blend well. Gradually, add sifted dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add vanilla and 1 cup hot water.
Blend until smooth.
Turn into 3 greased 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple, water and sugar to boil then remove from stove.
Add jello and chill until partially set.
Whip this slightly before adding other ingredients.
Beat cream cheese with milk.
Add Cool Whip, then add to jello mixture and chill.

title: lemon custard in cups
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add flour, salt, lemon juice and lemon zest.
Stir in milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 8 greased custard cups.
Set cups in warm bath 1/4 to 1/2-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Each cup will have custard on the bottom and cake on the top.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon (removing skin and bones). Combine with all ingredients, expect pecans and parsley. Chill several hours. Shape into roll of 8 x 2-inches long. Roll in nuts and parsley that have been mixed together. Chill well. This recipe is from an Alaskan fisherman and cannery operator.

title: chocolate chip nut bars
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Make paste from cocoa and vinegar and add to butter mixture.
Sift salt, baking soda and flour together and add to mixture with buttermilk, vanilla and food coloring.
Put in three greased pans. Bake at 350 degrees for about 35 minutes or until done.

title: crab on english muffin
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Add crab and stir until thickened.
Spread on English muffins.
Bake or broil until brown. Cut in quarters (bite-size pieces).

title: old fashioned green tomato relish
directions: Remove cores and chop all ingredients sized to grind in a food chopper.
Put in a large enamel pot or container not of tin or aluminum.
Add salt and let stand overnight.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onion and green peppers in oil until tender.
Add ground beef and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover the last 15 minutes of cooking. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar and let stand for 2 hours.
Bring orange juice to boil.
In a large bowl combine jello gelatin and orange juice.
Stir until all dissolved.
Add all other ingredients.

title: brunch strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add oil and eggs and mix thoroughly.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: kraut burgers
directions: Mix together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Have to grill; not tasteful any other way.

title: grilled portabella mushrooms and peppers
directions: Wash the mushrooms and pat dry. Trim the stem but leave it on. Marinate the mushrooms and peppers in your favorite marinade (or use the one below) for at least 1 hour.
Grill the mushrooms, turning occasionally and brushing with marinade, until very dark and cooked through, about 45 minutes, depending on the temperature of your grill.
Add the peppers in enough time to cook to taste (we like them slightly blackened).
Wash the watercress and arrange on a platter.
Place the mushrooms and peppers on the watercress.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat egg and add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour and add soda, salt and baking powder.
Then add a cup of lard.
Mix well; roll thin and cut.
Bake in a fairly hot 325° or 350° oven.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Get your favorite glass and a spoon.
Squirt as much chocolate syrup in your cup that you can get away with and add milk to fill your cup.
Stir well.
Drink this as fast as you can and ask to make more.
Don't ask to do this before dinner though because your mom will say "you can't have anything to drink because it will ruin your supper".

title: muffin cones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Set ice cream cones in cups of muffin pan.
Fill cones equally with batter.
Sprinkle some topping on cones.
Lightly press into batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Serve warm.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain. Mix rice, broccoli and soup. Saute celery and onions. Add to broccoli and soup mixture. Add Cheez Whiz. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: vanilla custard for pies
directions: Mix sugar, yolks and cornstarch.
Gradually add all milk, while stirring.
Cook in double boiler, on medium heat, until thick.
Add vanilla.
Add raisins or coconut.
Pour into 2 medium cooked pie shells.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers, in large bowl.
Pour in baking dish.
Add butter and crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shelley's cheesecake
directions: Spray a springform pan.
Preheat oven 350°.
Combine ingredients. Bake in oven for 1 hour.
Shut oven off and leave cake in oven with door open for 1 hour.

title: jello divinity
directions: Grease a jelly roll pan with butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding Jell-O gradually.
Continue to beat until Jell-O is dissolved.
Cook sugar, water and syrup to 252°, or until it spins a fine thread.
Pour the syrup into the egg mixture in a thin, fine stream, beating constantly until candy loses its gloss.
Pour into a greased pan at once.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: peppered dry rub(for steaks, chicken, roast, pork)
directions: Mix all seasoning in a zip lock bag. Wash and pat dry your meat of choice, place meat on a working tray or pan, you will need to be able to cover this. Poke holes in the meat on both sides, drizzle olive oil on meat and with a pastry brush spread it all over to coat. Next sprinkle the seasoning mix on the meat, making sure that the

entire meat is covered. Do this on both sides. Cover with wrap and place in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour. Cook meat on the grill for best results, but I have used this in the oven and it was really good.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour peaches over butter. Mix flour and sugar; add milk and stir out all lumps.
Pour flour, sugar and milk mixture over top of peaches and butter in back and forth motion.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: simple pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour slowly, mixing well.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together.
Add flour and mix well; shape into a ball.
Roll out on floured board and spread sausage on top.
Roll up into a long roll; chill in refrigerator, wrapped in foil for 3 to 4 hours.
Slice into pinwheels and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium saucepan over medium heat, cook fruit until boiling.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, 1 cup sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, melt margarine.
Pour batter over butter.
Add hot fruit.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over entire casserole.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix creamed corn and eggs well.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Place butter "pats" even on top of corn flakes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: overnight pickles
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, salt and seed until sugar is melted. Pour over cucumbers and onion in a large bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Put in jars next day.
These will store well for months if kept in the refrigerator.

title: bubble bread coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Place 1 dozen rolls in bottom of pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 box pudding.
Put in a handful of nuts. Repeat with remaining rolls. On top of stove, melt the margarine. Add sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over top of bread. Cover and let stand overnight on stove. Bake in morning at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: fruit bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine beaten eggs, milk and oil in large mixing bowl. Gradually add dry mixture until thoroughly combined.
Stir in carrots, coconut, cherries, raisins and pecans.
Turn into four 16 ounce fruit or vegetable cans that have been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from cans and cool thoroughly.
Wrap and refrigerate until used.
To make a large loaf, bake in a loaf pan 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple dairy salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple; add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Combine juice, marshmallows and jello.
Heat until marshmallows dissolve.
Cool until almost set; then fold in whipped topping.
Add nuts, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Pour into a 1-quart mold or bowl or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: valerie's popsicles
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water together in pitcher.
Pour into empty ice trays.
Freeze in freezer partially, then place ice cream sticks into mix.
Then freeze completely.
Just pop ice trays and serve a popsicle.

title: oriental green beans
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet over medium-low heat.
Drain on paper towel.
Cook onion and garlic in bacon grease until tender. Stir in soy sauce and add green beans.
Cook and stir until hot. Crumble bacon just before serving.
Stir in bacon.
Serves 4.

title: easy beef stew casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 3 hours.

title: chewies
directions: Melt butter and pour over sugar; cream.
Add eggs and flour. Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased pan at 325° or 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Save 1 cup of broth with cooked onion (boil onion with chicken).
Lay chicken in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix 2 cups of broth with can of soup. Pour over seasoned chicken meat.
Cut margarine into flour, then stir in milk.
Dribble this over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until crust is golden brown and bubbly.
(Milk and flour mixture will seem too liquid, but "trust me," it will solidify.)

title: homemade dreamsicles
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into trays and freeze until firm enough to eat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush crackers and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Save a few for top.
Melt oleo and pour over crackers.
Place chicken breasts on crackers.
Mix soups and sour cream together. Pour half the soup mixture on the chicken.
Layer water chestnuts on soup mixture.
Pour remaining soup mixture over water chestnuts.
Sprinkle with remaining crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: company potatoes(in memory of dickey lykins)
directions: Mix and put in a 9x13 baking dish.
Then sprinkle 2 cups of crushed corn flakes and 1/4 c. melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45-60 mins.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add crushed wafers alternately with milk.
Add coconut and pecans and mix well.
Pour into a 12-cup greased tube pan or a fluted pan sprayed with plenty of nonstick spray. Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
This cake freezes well.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Fill each cone with cake batter to within 1 inch of top. Place cones in muffin tins.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or as cupcake recipe directs.

title: cherries in the snow("elegant and easy")
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in cream and marshmallows.
Spread over meringue.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: new york clam chowder
directions: Brown bacon with onion.
When onion is soft, add tomatoes, salt, pepper, carrots, potatoes and water.
Boil until potatoes and carrots are done.
Add clams, thyme and clam juice.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: cracker candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk and bring to boil.
Combine crackers and peanut butter with milk and sugar.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Beat and pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator and cut in squares.
Eat!

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soften gelatine in water.
Make soup according to can directions, add gelatine to soup and cool.
In blender, combine 1/2 mixture with cheese, mayonnaise, then add the rest.
Blend again.
Pour liquid off shrimp.
Add to soup mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into tube pan, Bundt pan or other mold.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Serve with unsalted crackers (Carr's).

title: no-cook freezer jam
directions: You will also need 3 clean pint jars with covers.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in bacon drippings.
Mix all other ingredients in beans, adding onion and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake one hour at 250° to 300°.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Add finely chopped broccoli, onion, celery and lemon juice to 2 cups boiling water.
Cook until tender.
Do not drain; mash slightly.
Heat butter in 3-quart pan.
Blend in flour, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in the 2 1/2 cups of water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli mixture, salt (optional), pepper and bouillon cubes.
Heat again just to boiling.
Cut up 1 pound Velveeta cheese.
Add to mixture and heat to melt cheese.
Add cream; do not boil.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Saute scallops in butter or margarine for one minute only. Remove from pan and set aside.
Add wine to liquid in pan and simmer for a short time.
Return scallops to pan and mix into sauce.
Add scallop mixture to rice mixture and blend.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or under broiler until golden.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine pineapple and jello in saucepan.
Heat just until jello is dissolved. Remove from heat and stir in buttermilk, coconut and pecans. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill until firm.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Stir in milk; add butter. Melt butter mix on medium heat (may let boil 1 to 2 minutes).
Take off heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Add oats and stir until oats are coated by chocolate mixture.
Drop by spoonful on to wax paper.
Should be ready to eat in an hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Run cool water over to chill.
Mix vegetables and pasta and refrigerate overnight.
Mix with dressing when ready to serve.

title: all-in-one meat loaf dinner(this dish is similar in flavor to stuffed cabbage.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread the oil in a 14 x 11 x 3-inch baking pan. Add the cabbage, onion, tomatoes and sugar. Add salt and pepper and mix well.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all together; spread in pan.
Bake for about 25 minutes, or until golden.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Makes 4 dozen.
Freezes great!

title: chicken dijon
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes, or until browned.
Remove from skillet; pour off fat.
In same skillet, combine soup, water, mustard and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat for 5 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Stir often.
Serve with rice.

title: vanilla almond coffee
directions: Add extracts to coffee.
Shake to blend thoroughly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray Pam on baking dish and pour Minute rice over bottom (1/2 inch).
Cover with dots of butter and then Armour dried beef.
Lay deboned breasts on beef.
Mix sour cream with cream of celery soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, and 1/2 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: crisp chicken fingers
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In shallow bowl, combine cornflakes, garlic powder and dry mustard.
Dip chicken pieces in melted margarine; roll in cereal mixture, coating evenly.
Place in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and coating is crisp.
Serve warm with variety of dipping sauces, such as sweet and sour, honey mustard or barbecue sauce.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: applesauce bread pudding
directions: Spread toasted bread with butter and cut into quarters. Place buttered side up in greased 8 x 8 baking dish. Sprinkle raisins over toast. Mix eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, applesauce, evaporated milk and vanilla until well blended. Pour over toast. Let stand 10 minutes. Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: classic lobster seafood salad
directions: Mix Lobster Delights, mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blonde brickle brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.
Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat eggs well.
Add both sugars and beat until creamy.
Add melted butter and both extracts. Gently add flour mixture until all is moist.
Fold in 2/3 cup of Brickle Bits and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining Brickle Bits over top immediately.
Cool.
Cut into desired serving size.

title: cheesy fruit 'n nut spread
directions: Gradually add honey and orange juice to Neufchatel cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Cover; chill.

title: low-fat jello cheese pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix in jello and beat until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust and place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Before cutting cucumbers, take seeds out and peel.
Combine cucumbers, onions and red hot peppers; put on salt and let stand overnight.
Drain well and add remainder of ingredients.
Cook until tender; can hot.

title: clay dough for california relief map(non-edible)
directions: Carefully mix the ingredients in a large bowl.
Slowly add the hot water until you have a dough that is easy to shape and will not stick to your hands.
You may have to adjust the amount of flour and water you use until you have dough that is just right for molding.
Shape the dough into a ball and put it into a covered container until you are ready to spread it out on your map board.

title: egg salad spread
directions: Mix powdered mustard with about 1/2 teaspoon of warm ???.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
If you prefer softer spread, add a bit more mayonnaise.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fold together in a bowl the Veg-All, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups and chicken.
Spray a 9-inch pie pan lightly with Pam.
Unfold the first crust in place. Be sure to pierce the unbaked pie shell several times with a fork and then pour in the Veg-All, soup and chicken mixture.
Place the second pie crust on top.
Flute edges and pierce with fork.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Toss mushrooms, onions and parsley; just before serving, toss together cheese, vegetables and dressing.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese.
Add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
(You can leave out the nuts if you don't like them.)

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done (crumbled); drain.
Mix cheese and sausage; sprinkle in pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs in a bowl. Combine rest of ingredients to eggs and pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: one pan pie crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients in pie pan.
Make a hole in center and pour in the oil and milk.
Combine with a fork until well-blended. Pat dough evenly with the back of a spoon or hands.
Prick bottom and bake in preheated 425° oven for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except crackling.
Add the milk and stir in the crackling.
Pour into a greased 12-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: spaghetti or lasagna sauce
directions: Cook all together in saucepan until thickened; add 12 ounces tomato sauce.
Bring to boil.
Simmer on low 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: arroz con pollo(mexican rice with chicken)
directions: In a large skillet brown chicken 8 to 12 minutes.
In a small skillet brown the rice.
Add browned rice to chicken in the large skillet.
Add bell pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Blend well; add broth and water, then add garlic and ground cumin.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until water evaporates, then fluff rice with fork.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: german oven pancake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend well.
Place 1 1/2 cubes margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place in oven until butter melts and bubbles.
Pan and butter should be very hot.
Remove pan from oven and pour mixture in pan.
Return to oven.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake another 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour on topping and serve with fresh fruit/preserves.

title: slow cooked pork
directions: Place ribs and onion in slow cooker.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and cook on low setting for 10 to 12 hours or high setting for 5 to 6 hours.

title: easy rolls (or bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil and salt; mix well, adding flour last.
Let rise in a warm place, covered.
Form into desired shapes in greased cup cake pans or in pie plates. Let rise again, about 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. This dough may be used to make pizza shells.

title: penne
directions: Cook bacon (soft).
Set aside.
Saute onions until pale gold. Combine with bacon.
Saute 1 minute.
(Use bacon grease.)
Add tomatoes, pepper and salt.
Set aside.

title: mom's coconut cake
directions: Soften butter at room temperature. Mix butter and sugar together. Add one egg at a time, beating well. Add flavoring to butter and sugar mixture. Sift flour, baking powder and salt in separate bowl. Add flour, 1 cup at a time. Add milk as mixture gets stiff.

title: overnight macaroons
directions: Combine oatmeal, sugar and oil; let set overnight. Next day, add eggs, salt and flavoring; mix well. Drop by spoon onto well greased cookie sheet. Bake at 315° for 10 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from pan. Yields 6 dozen.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices.
Add to apples.
Fill 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 50 minutes.

title: ho bo's
directions: For each person cut 14 x 14-inch foil.
Place sliced potatoes, onions and hamburg on tinfoil in layers.
Place soup on top of layers.
Mix only 1/2 can water to soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add some soup over hamburg.
Bring corners of foil together and twist top.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with salad, etc.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.*
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 8 x2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)

title: amish cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: broccoli casserole dish
directions: Cook broccoli as on package.
Spray casserole dish.
Melt two sticks of butter and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Break up 1 1/2 packages of crackers and mix that in with broccoli, butter and cheese.
When mixed well, break up 1/2 package of crackers or more which ever way you like it.
Put that on top of broccoli mix then melt last stick of butter.
Pour that on top of crackers.
Cover it and cook in oven at 350° until cheese starts to bubble and it's golden brown, about 1/2 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, salt, pepper and milk with corn.
Place in buttered casserole and top with cracker crumbs.
Drip butter over crumbs and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven. Bake in individual ramekins, if you like. Serves 6.

title: mom's oven barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs in a greased roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cook for 1 minute.
Drain ribs. Spoon sauce over ribs.
Cover and bake for 1-1/2 hours.
Uncover; bake 30 minutes longer, basting once.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in lemon rinds, nuts, cinnamon, nutmeg and apples.
Blend into a creamed mixture, putting buttermilk in a little bit at a time.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: clam fritters
directions: Beat eggs until light; add milk.
Stir in flour and baking powder, seasonings and clams.

Drop by tablespoon into pan of fat heated to 375° or until 1-inch cube of bread browns in 1 minute. (Dip spoon in hot fat before using.) Fritters should be cooked through, browned on outside in 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Result, a light fluffy fritter.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni noodles until tender.
Drain.
In large bowl, mix tuna, noodles, chopped boiled eggs, herb dressing, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Serve as is or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut-potato-apple bake(low-fat)
directions: In a crock-pot, make 2 layers of all ingredients except cider. After layered, pour over apple cider.
Cook on high for 5 hours.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: To Make Stuffing:
Break bread into pieces.
Add onion and 1/2 of gravy to moisten.
Add celery and egg.
Mix.
Then score flank steak (you can have butcher do it for you).

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef or chicken and onion in large skillet, until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: potato spinach casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients except cheese.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes uncovered.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 5 more minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: parmesan cheese salad dressing
directions: Whip together lemon juice and pulp with finely chopped garlic clove.
Slowly mix in oil.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Mix in cheese after 1 hour.
Great with an Italian entree and a light and lively salad.

title: light bread buns
directions: Dissolve in water, dry yeast. Add all other ingredients.
Make stiff dough. Grease top and let rise until double size. Knead 4-5 min. Make small balls. Place in greased pan and let rise until double in size. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup,
milk and dash of pepper.
In Pam-sprayed 1 1/2 quart
casserole,
arrange
alternate layers of potatoes, onions, peppers,
soup
mixture and cheese.
Salt and pepper. Dot top with butter;
sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for
1 hour.
Uncover
and
bake 15 minutes more, if not done.

title: toffee squares
directions: Blend butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour and salt. Blend well.
Pat mixture into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Mixture will be soft, but lightly browned.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Mix crackers and 4 Tbsp margarine and press mixture into 8 inch pie plate.
Melt 2 Tbsp margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and saute for 12 minutes (add salt and pepper to taste).
Arrange onions in crust.
Beat milk and eggs in medium bowl.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 35 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Place lettuce in the bottom of an oblong 9 x 13-inch container, then green peppers, celery and peas on top.
Put mayonnaise on top of peas by spoonfuls.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate!
Marinate tomatoes in Italian dressing.
Put on top of cheese just before serving.
Then add sliced eggs and bacon last (on top).
Onions are optional!

title: irish soda bread
directions: Soak raisins 10 minutes in hot water, then drain dry.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add caraway seed and raisins.
Stir in eggs and buttermilk, gradually.
Dough will be moist.
No need to knead.

title: hershey bar chocolate cake
directions: Mix together. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes (test for doneness with toothpick). Cool for 10 minutes and remove from cake pans to finish cooling.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan over medium heat and bring to boil.
Boil 3 minutes and remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir in peanut butter.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square baking dish and let cool.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put everything into casserole dish and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add lobster meat and cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour and continue cooking 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add wine and cook until heated through.
Set aside.
Put remaining ingredients in blender, cover and blend at slow speed until mixed.
Add ingredients to lobster and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 4 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar, flour and pineapple juice, mixing well.
Add pineapple and cheese and stir.
Put mixture into casserole dish.
Mix together the crackers and butter and cover top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar and butter.
Stir well.
Add milk, slightly beaten eggs, vanilla and nutmeg, stirring well. Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: turkey sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet, saute turkey, onion and green pepper over medium heat for 5 minutes, until turkey is no longer pink.
Add catsup, relish, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, salt, garlic powder and celery seed.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
To serve, spoon turkey mixture over bottom halves of buns.
Place top halves of buns over turkey mixture.
Serves 8.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Spray a 10-inch pie plate with Pam.
Add hamburger mixture.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together; pour on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk and add cream cheese.
Cool; add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.

title: salad dressing
directions: In blender, mix anchovies, onion, celery and garlic.
Add Accent and peppercorns.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well. Gradually add Crisco oil alternating with lemon juice.
Put in container and chill.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all together and drop by tablespoon in pan with hot oil. Makes 8 crab cakes.

title: martha's breakfast
directions: Brown pork and drain, then crumble into 13 x 9-inch baking dish along with 6 slices of cubed bread.
Beat eggs, along with 2 cups milk.
Add grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can also add mushrooms, green peppers or bacon or ham instead of sausage.

title: sugar cream pie #1
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nutmeg) thoroughly until smooth. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top generously with nutmeg. Bake for 15 minutes at 450°, then reduce to 350° for 30 more minutes.

title: cranberry christmas wreath
directions: Wash, quarter and
seed the orange.
Put through medium blade of a food
grinder	together with raw cranberries.	Stir in sugar and chopped
nuts.	Chill several hours in refrigerator.

title: conestoga steak sauce
directions: Heat in microwave and marinate over steaks all day.
Fork steaks before marinating.
Use leftover sauce to dip steak in or to pour over steak.

title: pink punch
directions: Freeze all ingredients except 7-Up or ginger ale and raspberry sherbet like slush.
When ready to serve, add 7-Up or ginger ale and sherbet.
This fills a large punch bowl.

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into cupcake liners in muffin tins or into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: mixed bean rarebit
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda, nutmeg and salt and add to shortening/egg mixture.
Add apples to batter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze in muffin tin with cupcake liners.

title: caramel fudge jumbles
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, oats and peanuts.
Set aside.
In medium saucepan over low heat or a double boiler, melt caramels and mix with water.
Pour over cereal mix; toss until well coated.
Press mixture in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate and butterscotch chips evenly over cereal mixture.
Bake in 200° oven for 5 minutes.
Spread melted chips evenly
over bars.
Cool 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: cake brownies
directions: Spray a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick coating; set pan aside.
In a medium saucepan, melt the margarine.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the sugar and cocoa powder until combined.
Add egg white and vanilla to saucepan.
Using a wooden spoon, lightly beat just until combined.
Add flour, milk, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat with the spoon until combined.
Stir in walnuts or pecans.
Spread the batter into the prepared baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 16 to 18 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Sprinkle with the powdered sugar.
Drizzle the Chocolate Icing; let stand for 30 minutes or until icing is set.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine in glass bowl. Microwave on high for 3 minutes. Whip with wire whisk until smooth.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix soup, dressing and preserves to make a sauce. Pour over chicken breast. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cornell bread
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a measuring cup; add flour to make 1 cup.

title: fried rice
directions: *Make sure rice is cooked and cooled.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place breast between wax paper.
Pound until 1/4-inch thick. Spread mustard on chicken and top with cheese and ham.
Leave about 1/4-inch around edge of chicken.
Brush edge with egg.
Fold in half.
Press to seal.
Dip in flour mixed with salt and pepper, then egg, then crumbs.
Place on wire rack and refrigerate for 30 minutes to allow crumbs to set.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil.
Add onion and tomatoes and continue to saute.
Add vegetables and pour hot water on rice.
Let cook on medium heat until done (20 to 25 minutes).
Add salt to taste.

title: german apple cake
directions: Place chopped apples in lightly salted water while you prepare the batter.
Beat together oil and white and brown sugars; add eggs one at a time until well blended.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to sugar-egg mixture, mixing well.
Stir in well drained apples, nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly in lightly oiled and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325°
about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool in pan 20 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool completely.
Drizzle glaze over cake before serving.

title: jelly pie
directions: Beat egg yellows.
Add	rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked
pie
shell.
Bake	like
custard
pie.
When
desired firmness is attained in 400° oven for 10 minutes, then in 300° to 325° oven until done.
Finish with meringue made from 3 egg whites.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and rinse spaghetti.
Layer spaghetti with chicken and sauce.
Crunch Doritos on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Makes a large casserole.)

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt oleo and mix in crumbs.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Set in refrigerator and chill until ready for next layer.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Drain beans, but keep liquid.
Place the drained beans in a casserole dish.
Add the other ingredients and about 1 cup of reserved liquid.
Stir gently using a rubber spatula to keep from breaking up the beans.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: enchilada casserole(mexican)
directions: Saute onions in butter, do not brown.
Add tomato sauce, chili peppers, Italian seasoning and celery salt.
Simmer 5 minutes. Lightly beat eggs, add cream and mix well.
Remove tomato mixture from heat, quickly stir in egg and cream
mixture.
Cover the bottom of a 2-quart casserole with 1/3 of the Jack cheese, cubed. Add a layer of tortillas, torn into pieces.
Top with sauce, then repeat layers.
Spread sour cream over top and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until bubbly hot.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: curried or spiced fruit
directions: Drain and combine canned fruits.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and flavorings.
Stir into the fruit.
Cover and heat in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir in bananas just before serving.
Use any combination of fresh and canned fruits: cherries, grapes, mandarin oranges, etc.

title: vanilla wafers no. 2
directions: Cream butter.
Add the sugar and unbeaten eggs.
Beat until thoroughly blended, then add vanilla.
Drop one teaspoonful on a greased baking sheet, allowing 2 inches for spreading.
Bake in moderate oven at 330°, about 2 minutes.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: In mixing bowl, using a pastry cutter, mix together shortening, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. In small bowl, whisk together the egg, water and vinegar. Stir into dry ingredients. Cover and chill at least 3 hours (overnight is best). If dough is rolled out thin, recipe will yield 2 double-crust pies.

title: no bake banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and mix with crumbs.
Spread into 9-inch cake pan.
In mixing bowl, cream 1 stick butter, eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread over crumbs in pan.
Slice bananas and spread over sugar mixture.
Drain pineapple well and spread over bananas.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle nuts over top.
Garnish with cherries.
Refrigerate until cool.
Keep refrigerated.
